Commentary: Afridi starts with a fuller ball, outside off and hint of inward shape. Fernando drives it to the man at covers.
A full ball but down the leg side. Oshada Fernando fails to flick it away.

A huge appeal for LBW but not given! This one lands on a length and around middle and it swings back in late. Oshada Fernando fails to read as it comes back in and hits him high on the pads. Height might be the issue there.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Sri Lanka and Oshada Fernando are underway! Short of a length and outside off, Oshada Fernando cuts it hard and through point for a boundary.
FOUR! Gorgeous drive! This one comes nicely onto the bat Fuller and outside off. Oshada Fernando leans and drives it through covers for a boundary.
On a length and on off. Oshada Fernando blocks it out.
Hasan Ali starts with a full delivery, down the leg. Dimuth Karunaratne misses his flick.
This is full and way outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne leaves it alone.
On a length and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne knocks it towards covers for a single. He gets off the mark.
Good length and outside off, Oshada Fernando cuts it but straight to point.
Full again but down the leg, Oshada Fernando fails to flick it away. Hasan Ali is struggling to find the right line here.
Full delivery on the pads, Oshada Fernando helps it towards fine leg for a single.
Too full from Afridi, around off. Oshada Fernando puts a nice foot forward to drive it to covers.
On the pads, it is flicked to square leg for one more. It went off the pads so given as a leg bye.
Afridi is just a bit erring with his line! He is trying to swing back in but fails again here. This is on a length and angling down the leg side. Dimuth Karunaratne misses his flick.
Touch fuller and outside off. Karunaratne steps across to push but gets a thick inside edge onto the pads and it rolls to mid on.
Length ball on off. Karunaratne taps it in front of covers.

OUT! TIMBER! Shaheen Afridi gets his man and does his trademark celebration! This is on a length and outside off, it nips back in off the deck. Karunaratne prods across to push but does so with hard hands and the ball movement trims the inside edge, takes a bit of pad before shattering the stumps. Pakistan get the opening wicket quite early.
Howout: b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary: Bye! Fuller and way down the leg side. Fernando fails to play at it. The keeper does well to get a hand on it. A single.
Tad full and on middle. Blocked out.
On a length and on top of off. Mendis drops it to covers and runs across for a quick single. He is off the mark.
This time Fernando tries the same thing, drop and run but hits it straight to the man at covers.
Short of a length and on off. Fernando defends with a straight bat.
Length ball way outside off. Fernando makes an easy leave.
A short ball, around leg. Mendis sits under it.
Darted on the pads, tucked to deep square leg for one more.
Length ball, outside off, late away swing. Fernando shoulders arms to it.
Tight from Afridi! length and on middle. Fernando blocks it out on the deck.
Bangs a bouncer on middle. Fernando rides it as he pulls it to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
On a length and outside off, not much swing there. Left alone.
Fuller ball, outside off, hint of away shape. Mendis lets it go.
Angles a length ball on middle and leg. Mendis stays behind to keep it out.
Quick single! Length and outside off. Mendis punches it wide of covers for a sharp single.
Length and on the pads. Fernando nudges it to deep square leg for a single.
Pitched up on middle. Mendis drives it but straight to mid on.
Outside off, Mendis shoulders arms to it.
Too straight on middle. Fernando whips it behind square on the leg side for a brace. Good running.
Outside off on a length, punched to mid off.
Hits the hard length, outside off. Fernando keeps it out.
Goes fuller now, outside off. Fernando defends it out.
FOUR! Oshada Fernando is looking in good shape here! Again this is too straight from Afridi, on middle. Oshada Fernando wrists it past mid-wicket and mid on for a boundary.
Overpitched and on off. Fernando drives it to mid off.
On a length and on off at 133 kph. Mendis gets behind the line to block it. Shah overstepped and a no ball is given.
Outside off, on a length. Mendis shoulders arms.
Gets this to swing back in but the line is outside off. Mendis watchfully lets it through to the keeper.
On top of off. Mendis blocks it out.
Fuller and outside off. Mendis guides it to point.
FOUR! Good shot! On a length and outside off. Mendis punches off the back foot, times it really well past point for four.
On off, blocked out.
On middle, on a length. Fernando makes a solid block again.
Afridi keeps the same line on middle. Fernando negotiates it well as he defends with his bat and pad together.
Fuller and on middle. Fernando drives it to the right of Afridi who gets a hand on it and deflects it away from mid on for a couple of runs.
Pitches it up on off. Fernando pushes it to mid off.

Good shot again! Short in length and outside off. Fernando opens the face of the bat and guides it through the gully region. The fielder from backward point gives a chase and pulls it back right near the ropes. Really good work there. A couple.
On the pads. Fernando tucks it to square leg.
Fuller ball on off. Mendis blocks it to covers.
Length ball on middle. Mendis gets behind the line again to defend it.
FOUR! Mendis looks in good touch here as well! Overpitched and outside off. Mendis leans and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
A length ball on middle. Mendis tucks it to square leg for a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the keeper's end but misses.
On middle, kept out by Oshada Fernando!
Yasir Shah begins with a full delivery on middle, Kusal Mendis knocks it towards mid off.
This one is full and pitching on leg, Kusal Mendis taps it to the left of short leg.
Flighted full and pitching on leg, Kusal Mendis defends and gets an inside edge towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Serves a full delivery on the pads, Oshada Fernando flicks this through square leg for a single.
Yasir Shah goes full outside off, Kusal Mendis defends this to the cover fielder.
This one is a fraction short in line with the stumps, Kusal Mendis nudges it through mid-wicket for a single.
Naseem Shah bowls this on a good length outside off, Kusal Mendis fends this towards short cover.
On a good length and just outside off, Kamindu Mendis taps it back to the left of the bowler.
Goes fuller this time outside off, Kusal Mendis defends this solidly towards the cover fielder.
Naseem Shah goes full and angles the ball into the pads, Kusal Mendis taps this towards mid-wicket with soft hands and rushes across for a single.
Back to bowling on a good length outside off, Oshada Fernando stands tall and knocks it back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery on a middle stump line, Oshada Fernando guides it wide of mid-wicket for a single.
Yasir Shah fires this one in full on the pads, Oshada Fernando pushes this towards short leg. Falls just short of the fielder.

FOUR! Oshada Fernando shimmies down the wicket and catches the ball on the full and on middle, lofts the ball over mid on. It is not timed well and just clears the fielder to run towards the wide long on boundary for four runs! Oshada Fernando is playing well here!
Full delivery in line with the stumps, defended back down the pitch by Oshada Fernando.
This one is full and pitching on leg, Oshada Fernando looks to work it leg side and finds the short leg fielder.
Full outside off, Oshada Fernando takes a stride forward and defends it towards cover.

Huge appeal from the Pakistan players! Yasir Shah fires this one a fraction short and outside off, Oshada Fernando gets across the stumps to fend this on his back foot but gets hit on the pads first before hitting his bat. The umpire remains unmoved and there is a discussion on whether or not to review. Eventually, they decide against taking it and it seems like a good decision as the ball seems to have made an impact outside the off-stump line.
Naseem Shah bangs this one in short and angles it into the body. Kusal Mendis pulls and mistimes it. The ball reaches on a bounce to the wide fine leg fielder. They take a run in the process.
On a good length outside off, Oshada Fernando is happy to leave this one alone.
FOUR! This one is trickled fine! Naseem Shah angles this down the pads from a good length, Oshada Fernando gets bat to the ball and it goes running towards the fine leg boundary for four more runs!
Full and in line with the stumps, Oshada Fernando defends this back to the bowler who parries it towards mid on.
This one is on a good length and straight towards the stump. Oshada Fernando knocks this firmly towards mid on.
Naseem Shah goes a fraction full outside off, Oshada Fernando fends this straight to the cover fielder.
Yasir Shah begins with a full delivery on leg, Kusal Mendis fends this towards mid on.
FOUR! Kusal Mendis gets this away! Yasir Shah tosses this up full and on middle, Kusal Mendis gets on his knees and sweeps this towards deep square leg for a boundary!
Full outside off, Kusal Mendis guides this past point for a single.
Yasir Shah floats this one full and angling into the pads. Oshada Fernando paddles this fine towards fine leg for three runs.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Yasir Shah strikes for Pakistan and this should get his confidence up! He pulls his length back and bowls it outside off, Kusal Mendis goes for to slash this square but gets a faint top edge to the keeper. Mohammad Rizwan takes a sharp catch behind the wicket and Kusal Mendis turns around and walks away. Sri Lanka have lost their second wicket and need to build a partnership here if they have to set up a good first innings total!
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Yasir Shah

Commentary: Yasir Shah goes short once again and closer to the stumps. Angelo Mathews defends this solidly back to the bowler.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Back to back wickets for Pakistan. This time it is Hasan Ali who gets into the act. He bowls it on a length outside off, shaping away a bit. Oshada Fernando tries to play at it without any footwork and the ball takes his outside edge and goes to the keeper. Mohammad Rizwan completes a sharp catch as he dives to his right. Sri Lanka in trouble now as two new batsman are in right now.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Hasan Ali

Commentary: Full and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal blocks it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, outside off, shaping away. Dinesh Chandimal leaves it alone.
Full and drifting into the pads, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it through square leg for a couple of runs.
Good length and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal offers no shot at it.
On a length and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal knocks it straight to mid off.
Tossed up on leg, Angelo Mathews pushes it to mid on.
Floated on middle, Angelo Mathews blocks it with the inner half of his bat towards mid-wcket
Tossed up again on middle, Angelo Mathews defends it to the off side.
Just short! This is slower through the air on middle, turning away a bit. Angelo Mathews tries to defend it but the ball gets a thin outside edge but goes on the bounce to first slip.

Oh! This is a chance again. Yasir Shah drops it short on middle and off, Angelo Mathews punches it hard and straight to silly point. It was hit really hard and the fielder had no time to react. He gets hit on his left thigh.
On middle, blocked out.
Good length and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal leaves it alone.
Goes full this time on off, Dinesh Chandimal drives it straight to covers.
Bangs in short and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal ducks under it.
Fullish and outside off again, swinging away. Dinesh Chandimal lets it go to the keeper.
Another easy leave for Dinesh Chandimal as this is bowled outside off again.
Full and on leg, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it through square leg for a run.
Floated on middle and leg, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it to mid-wicket and denies the single.
A bit short and outside off, turning away a bit. Dinesh Chandimal guides it straight to point.
Full and on off, Dinesh Chandimal drives it to covers.
On middle, blocked out.
Quicker and flatter on off, Dinesh Chandimal plays it towards covers.
BEAUTY! This is slower through the air on off, turning away. Dinesh Chandimal comes forward for the defense but gets beaten on his outside edge by the late turn.
Full and on middle and leg, Angelo Mathews knocks it to mid on.
CLOSE! Hasan Ali bowls it on a length outside off, nips back in sharply. Angelo Mathews leaves it thinking that it would go the other way. The ball just misses the off pole.
Full and on off, shaping away this time. Angelo Mathews pushes it to covers.
Hasan Ali bowls it short and on off, Angelo Mathews gets behind it and defends it to the off side.
On a length and on off, swinging away. Angelo Mathews decides to leave it alone.
Goes fuller and on off, Angelo Mathews blocks it down the pitch.
Yasir Shah tosses this one full outside off, Dinesh Chandimal defends this towards cover.

FOUR! What a beautiful cover drive from Dinesh Chandimal! Yasir Shah flights this full outside off, Dinesh Chandimal gets his front foot forward and thumps it in the gap between cover and mid off to find the deep cover boundary and collect four runs!
Yasir Shah goes full on the pads, Dinesh Chandimal sweeps and finds the short fine leg fielder. A misfield allows the batters to take a single.
A fraction short outside off, Angelo Mathews defends this towards cover.

OUT! CAUGHT! The pressure builds on Angelo Mathews and he departs on a duck! Angelo Mathews seemed to be struggling at the wicket! Yasir Shah flights this one full on middle, Angelo Mathews does not get to the pitch of the delivery and tries to loft it over mid on. He does not get a hold of it and lobs it straight to Naseem Shah at mid on who makes no mistake pouching an easy catch! Sri Lanka are in big trouble here!
Howout: c Naseem Shah b Yasir Shah

Commentary: Short this time and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva goes on his back foot and defends it towards the offside.
Bangs this in short outside off, The ball does not rise much and Dinesh Chandimal pulls this towards square leg for a brace.
Hasan Ali serves this on a good length outside off, Dinesh Chandimal raises his hands and lets it through to the keeper.
Goes full and angles this into the stumps, Dinesh Chandimal flicks this through mid-wicket for a single.
On a good length once again but really wide from off stump. Dhananjaya de Silva leaves this alone.
This on is also bowled on a length outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva shoulders his arms to this one as well.
Bowls this full on the pads, Dhananjaya de Silva guides this to the mid-wicket fielder.
This one lands outside leg and spins away sharply from a fuller length. Dinesh Chandimal looks to defend but gets beaten and gets hit on the pads. Some extra bounce off the pitch as well.
Yasir Shah goes full outside off, Dinesh Chandimal punches this to the right of mid off and rushes across for a single.
Pulls his length back, and delivers this outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva knocks this towards point.
Short once again and pitching in line with the stumps. Dhananjaya de Silva is off the mark with a single towards mid-wicket.
Full and fired into the pads, Dinesh Chandimal digs this out and gets a leading edge towards mid off.
Slower in the air and flighted full outside off, Dinesh Chandimal fends this towards cover.
Hasan Ali serves this on a good length outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva carves this through cover-point and picks up three runs. Just a gentle tap through the gaps.
On a good length, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal stands tall and knocks it towards mid off.
Good-length delivery served outside off, Dinesh Chandimal guides this to cover-point.
Hasan Ali goes straight on a good length. Dinesh Chandimal defends firmly towards mid off.
Slower delivery bowled full and on an off stump line, Dinesh Chandimal plays this towards short mid-wicket.
This one is also a fraction full outside off, Dinesh Chandimal uses his wrists and works this towards mid on.
Yasir Shah begins with a short delivery pitching on leg and getting it to turn sharply. Dhananjaya de Silva fends this off his backfoot to the offside.
Yasir Shah bowls this full outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva taps it towards short cover.
Full and flighted into the pads, Dhananjaya de Silva knocks this to the cover fielder.
FOUR! Beautifully executed stroke by Dhananjaya de Silva! Flighted full and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva gets slightly forward and punches this through the gap at cover-point for a boundary!
Yasir Shah goes short to compensate and in line with the stumps. Dhananjaya de Silva uses the crease and pulls this straight to the mid-wicket fielder.
Full delivery drifting onto middle. Dhananjaya de Silva gets on his front foot and defends solidly! That will be LUNCH on Day 1!
Fuller ball on off. Chandimal blocks it out solidly.
FOUR! Good shot by Chandimal! Overpitched and on off. Chandimal drives it past the bowler, mid on gives a chase but the ball races away quickly into the fence.
Pushes it full and around off. Dinesh blocks it out.
FOUR! Two boundaries already in this new session! Tries the short one but too much width here. Chandimal hops and guides it past point for another boundary.
On a driving length, outside off. Chandimal is not tempted as he shoulders arms.
Angles a full ball on off. Chandimal steps across and forces it to mid on.
Tossed up on off, turning away. Dhananjaya de Silva punches it through cover-point for a run.
Serves it full and outside off. Chandimal lunges to defend.
Slows it up, full and on off. Chandimal prods and makes a solid block.
Gives a bit of flight this time, full and outside off, pushed to covers.
Flighted delivery, too full and on off, Dinesh drives it to mid off.
A flatter ball, on middle, probably a googly. Chandimal defended the wrong line and gets an inside edge, well past short leg for a brace.
Full and outside off. De Silva mistimes his drive completely and plays it back to the bowler.
This time De Silva times it well but can't get it past the man at mid off.
Full and slanting outside off. De Silva hangs back to block it.
Hits the hard length, outside off. De Silva drops it on the off side.
Very full and on middle. De Silva does well to get his bat down and squeeze it back to Afridi.
Angles it around off but De Silva negotiates it well as he pushes it back to the bowler. There is no movement for the seamers and looks like it will be spinners who will do the talking from here on.
Three taken! Floated, full and outside off, slows it up. Chandimal looks to defend but it turns away and takes the outside edge. It goes past first slip and to third man for three runs.
On off, pushed to mid off.
Slightly short and on top of off. De Silva rocks back and punches it to covers.
Flatter and on middle. Blocked out.
FOUR! Uses the feet nicely! This is too full and nicely floated. De Silva comes down the track and smashes it past mid off for a boundary.
Again uses his feet! This time De Silva fails to hit it past mid on but will get a single.
Drops it on a length and around off. De Silva tucks it to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on middle, whipped straight to short mid-wicket.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! The 31-run stand is broken and Sri Lanka have lost half of their team now! Dhananjaya de Silva was struggling to time the ball and it does not help here! Afridi steams in and serves a full ball, outside off. It is there to drive and De Silva goes with the shot but is a bit late and the ball ricochets back onto the stumps. Shaheen Afridi is a happy man as he begins his trademark celebration!
Howout: b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary: Just short! Fuller and outside off, nips a bit away. Dickwella looks to drive but gets an outside edge and it bounces just in front of the fielder at second slip.
Around off, fuller, pushed to covers.

FOUR! Fortunate one! Afridi keeps the same length and bowls it outside off. Dickwella tries to drive with soft hands but gets an outside edge and to the left of the diving second slip fielder for a boundary.
Shorter and on off, punched off the back foot to the bowler.
Slower and angling on the pads. Dinesh Chandimal keeps it out.
Tossed up, outside off, pushed to covers.
Flights it up, around off, pushed back to Shah.
A googly on off. Shah almost had Chanidmal there but the batter was quick to defend it.
A leg-spinner now! This is full and around off. Chndimal has to play it as he tries to defend but it lands and trims past the outside edge. Beautiful bowling from Shah, mixing his lines really well.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Dickwella goes now! What a spell this is from Afridi! Serves a full ball, angling outside off. Niroshan Dickwella rocks back to drive but gets a thick outside edge to Agha Salman who is standing at the widish fourth slip. He dives to his right and takes a low diving catch. A brilliant effort by the debutant there! Pakistan right on top here.
Howout: c Agha Salman b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary: Fuller and on off. Mendis pushes it to covers.
The ball is holding a bit here! This is full and around off. Mendis defends right under his eyes.
FOUR! That is superb from Mendis! Touch fuller on this occasion, just outside off. Mendis gets on the front foot and drives it firmly through covers for a boundary.
Very full and drifting around off. Mendis gets a soft leading edge to covers as he tries to work it on the leg side.
On the pads, nudged to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, driven to covers for a run.
Flatter and outside off, no spin on offer. Mendis leaves it alone.
Tossed up on off, Mendis works it to covers.
Tosses it up again. Kept out.
Flighted full and around middle and off. Mendis strides forward and blocks it out.
A loopy ball on middle, forced to mid on for a quick single.
Full ball on middle. Ramesh wrists it to mid-wicket.
A bouncer from Afridi after a long time. Mendis ducks under it.
The idea is right from Afridi but Mendis have done well so far! Afridi keeps bowling fuller and angling around off. Anticipating Mendis might mistime one or miss it but keeps it out again.
On middle, fuller, eased down to mid on.
Again tries the same thing but errs a bit and serves a low full toss on off. Mendis drills it past mid-wicket for a single.
Too full and outside off. Chandimal drives it straight to mid off.
Tossed up on leg. Mendis blocks it out.
Pushed through quicker and on middle. Mendis defends on the front foot.
Flatter ball, outside off, played back to the bowler.
Lands one too full and on off. Mendis drills it to mid on.
Gets this to turn away on a fuller length but Mendis prods and watchfully blocks it.
A quicker ball to end the over, fuller and on middle, Ramesh fends it to mid on.
Naseem Shah begins with a full delivery outside off, Dinesh Chandimal strokes this to the left of mid off.
Goes full once again and closer to the stumps, Dinesh Chandimal defends this to the mid off fielder.
Continues bowling full and this time in line with the stumps. Dinesh Chandimal fends this back to the bowler.
Pulls his length back to a good length outside off, Dinesh Chandimal knocks it back to the bowler.
Naseem Shah goes a fraction short outside off, Dinesh Chandimal covers the line of the ball and punches it to mid off.

FOUR! Dinesh Chandimal seems to be playing on a different pitch! This is served on a good length outside off, Dinesh Chandimal opens the face of the bat and guides it past point to get a wonderful boundary to deep cover-point.
Yasir Shah flights this full on middle, Ramesh Mendis defends this back to the bowler.
Drifts the ball in and gets it to pitch outside leg, Turns sharply, and hits Ramesh Mendis on the pads. Stifled appeal from the Pakistan players.
Tossed up full outside off, Ramesh Mendis defends this towards cover.
Full delivery pitching in line with the stumps and turning away. Ramesh Mendis opens the face of the bat and works it past slip for a brace.
Yasir Shah serves this short and turns from middle, Ramesh Mendis flicks this towards mid on.
Short once again outside off, This one is guided towards mid-wicket.
Naseem Shah serves this back of a length outside off, Dinesh Chandimal punches off his back foot towards mid off.
On a good length outside off, Dinesh Chandimal taps this towards short mid on.
Good-length delivery outside off, Dinesh Chandimal strokes this straight to the mid off fielder.
Naseem Shah goes full this time outside off, Dinesh Chandimal strokes this to the left of mid off, a good stop by the fielder to restrict the batters to a single.
Naseem Shah bowls this on a good length outside off, Ramesh Mendis defends this back to the bowler.
Short this time and outside off, Ramesh Mendis cuts the ball straight to the point fielder.
Yasir Shah flights this full on middle and leg, Dinesh Chandimal fends this back to the bowler.

FOUR! A boundary after a while for Sri Lanka! Yasir Shah tosses this full and pitching on leg, Dinesh Chandimal decides to sweep and gets a hold of it to send it towards the deep square leg boundary for four runs!
This one is tossed up full on middle. Dinesh Chandimal gets forward and fends it towards mid on.
Full once again but outside off this time, Dinesh Chandimal hits this to the left of mid off and completes a single.
Yasir Shah flights this and bowls it full and angling into the pads, Ramesh Mendis looks to defend and gets an inside edge towards deep backward square leg for a brace.
This is flighted full on off, Ramesh Mendis gets forward and defends solidly.
Mohammad Nawaz begins with a tossed-up delivery full outside off, Dinesh Chandimal knocks this towards cover.
Full once again outside off, Dinesh Chandimal taps it towards covers with soft hands and rushes across for a single. Good response from Ramesh Mendis as he gets home safe.
Goes a fraction short in line with the stumps, Ramesh Mendis guides it to mid on.
Short delivery wide from off stump, Ramesh Mendis goes back in his crease and slaps it to deep cover-point for a single.
Mohammad Nawaz serves this full once again outside off, Dinesh Chandimal fends this towards short mid off.
Flighted full outside off, Dinesh Chandimal works this towards cover-point and takes another good single.

Naseem Shah pulls his length back a bit, Dinesh Chandimal gets on top of it and pushes it through covers for three runs. The fielder at covers gives chase and does well to stop it from going for a boundary.
Bangs in a sharp bouncer on middle, Ramesh Mendis ducks under it.
Goes for the short ball again but this time on leg stump. Ramesh Mendis ducks again.
Three bouncers in a row. Naseem Shah bowls this one short on middle and leg, Ramesh Mendis is not interested in playing that.
On a length and on middle, Ramesh Mendis flicks it straight to mid-wicket.
Short again on the leg stump. Ramesh Mendis moves across and lets it go.
Shortish and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal punches of his back foot straight to extra covers.
Short again outside off, Dinesh Chandimal works this one through covers.
Floated on middle, blocked out.
Goes short again outside off, Dinesh Chandimal cuts it straight to short covers.
Tossed up full on off, Dinesh Chandimal knocks it to mid off.
Full again on off, Dinesh Chandimal opens the face and guides it to point. That is a maiden over from Mohammad Nawaz.
Naseem Shah is making his plans clear. Bowls a bouncer again on middle. Ramesh Mendis ducks underneath it.
Good-length delivery on middle, Ramesh Mendis pushes it past short leg but refuses the single.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! The plan has worked for Pakistan. Naseem Shah gets his man. He goes 'round the wicket and bowls another short ball on the leg stump. Ramesh Mendis this time tries to be aggresive and goes for the pull but the ball kisses his gloves and goes straight to the keeper. Mohammad Rizwan takes a simple catch moving to his left.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Naseem Shah

Commentary: Naseem Shah bowls a short ball from 'over the wicket. Prabath Jayasuriya ducks under it.
Well Bowled! Naseem Shah goes for the yorker and gets it right on the money, angling in onto the stumps. Prabath Jayasuriya does well to dig it out.
Full and drifting into the pads, Prabath Jayasuriya flicks it through square leg for a single and gets off the mark.
Shortish and around off, Prabath Jayasuriya pushes it to covers.

EDGED BUT SAFE! This is slower through the air on middle, turning away. Prabath Jayasuriya uses his feet to play at it but only manages a thick outside edge. The ball goes past the first slip fielder towards the vacant third man area. They get two runs.
Tossed up around off, Prabath Jayasuriya offers no shot at it.
On middle, blocked out.
Fullish delivery on off, Prabath Jayasuriya defends it well.

OUT! PLUMB IN FRONT! Mohammad Nawaz gets his first wicket of the match. He bowls this quicker and flatter on middle and leg, turning away. Prabath Jayasuriya is caught in the crease and misses the ball completely as he plays down the wrong line, misjudging the turn. It hits him on his pads right in front of the stumps. The fielders appeal for the LBW and up goes the finger. Prabath Jayasuriya is not even thinking of the review as he knows this is plumb. Sri Lanka eight down now.
Howout: lbw b Mohammad Nawaz

Commentary: Naseem Shah goes 'round the wicket and bangs it in short outside leg, Dinesh Chandimal ducks under this awkwardly.
Goes a fraction full down leg side, Dinesh Chandimal flicks this towards fine leg and does not take a single as he thinks the ball has gone for a boundary. Straight to the fielder though.
Naseem Shah goes short this time and angles it into the body from outside leg. Dinesh Chandimal ducks well under this.
FOUR! This one has been clobbered! Naseem Shah goes short from outside leg, This does not rise much and sits up nicely for Dinesh Chandimal to power this to the mid-wicket fence for a boundary!

FOUR! Make it two in a row! This is an action replay! The short ball ploy not working out for Naseem Shah! Dinesh Chandimal looks in fine touch as he dismisses this once again to the mid-wicket fence for four more runs.

FOUR! Make that three in a row! Naseem Shah goes a fraction fuller but this is also on the legs, Dinesh Chandimal clips this towards deep square leg for a one-bounce boundary! Brings up a wonderful half-century! He has been the rock for Sri Lanka and they will be hoping he continues batting this way. He is running out of partners but amidst all the chaos he has looked a class apart!
Full delivery outside off, Maheesh Theekshana gets forward and defends well.
Full and angled into the stumps, Maheesh Theekshana defends this towards cover.
Goes full once again outside off, Maheesh Theekshana pushes it towards mid off.
Beaten! Mohammad Nawaz tosses this up full outside off, gets the ball to rip and beat the outside edge.
Full and outside off, Maheesh Theekshana steady in defense this time.
Full outside off, Maheesh Theekshana works this towards cover. Another maiden from Mohammad Nawaz!
Naseem Shah bangs this in short and way down leg stump, Dinesh Chandimal does not bother to play at it.
Short once again but with better direction as it is angled into the batter. Dinesh Chandimal ducks under this one.
Delivers this on a good length aimed for the pads, Dinesh Chandimal works this through square leg for a single.
Goes over the wicket now and full outside off, Maheesh Theekshana looks to defend and gets a thick edge through point for a single.
Really short from Naseem Shah and going down leg, Dinesh Chandimal looks to pull and is quite far from it.

FOUR! Dinesh Chandimal is dealing in boundaries here! This is short as well and angled down leg, Dinesh Chandimal pulls this wide of fine leg for a well-placed boundary! He is playing a gem of an innings and helps bring up 150 runs for Sri Lanka.
Full and angled into the pads, Maheesh Theekshana knocks it towards mid off and rushes across for a single as he sees the fielder on his heels.
Mohammad Nawaz flights this full outside off, Dinesh Chandimal taps it down to the left of the bowler.
A fraction short and in line with the stumps, Dinesh Chandimal punches it back to the bowler's right as he dives to stop the ball.
Goes shorter and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal works this towards mid-wicket for a single.
Mohammad Nawaz continues bowling full in line with the stumps. Maheesh Theekshana fends it down the pitch.
This is full outside off, Maheesh Theekshana guides it towards point.
Yasir Shah begins with a flighted delivery full outside off, Dinesh Chandimal works this to long off for a single.
Full outside off, Maheesh Theekshana fends this towards cover.
Flighted full once again outside off, Maheesh Theekshana pushes at it and gets a thickish edge towards backward point.
A fraction short outside off, Maheesh Theekshana looks to slash this and finds the point fielder.
Short once again outside off, Maheesh Theekshana goes on his back foot and punches it to cover.
Yasir Shah flights this full on middle. Maheesh Theekshana defends this back to the bowler.

SIX! That is a cracking hit! Mohammad Nawaz goes full in line with the stumps, and Dinesh Chandimal goes down on one knee and lofts it over deep square leg for a biggie! Dinesh Chandimal is following up a wonderful innings in the last game with a crucial knock here!
Full once again outside off, defended back to the bowler.
Mohammad Nawaz serves this full outside off, Dinesh Chandimal works this to deep cover for a single.
Middle stump line and bowled full. Maheesh Theekshana defends this down the pitch.
FOUR! Maheesh Theekshana is tired of defending! Mohammad Nawaz flights this as well full outside off, Maheesh Theekshana gets a good stride forward and pounds it to deep cover for his first boundary!
Mohammad Nawaz serves this full outside off, Maheesh Theekshana leaves this one alone.
Yasir Shah begins slightly short outside off, Dinesh Chandimal slashes this straight to point.
Short once again and on a middle stump line. Dinesh Chandimal goes back in the crease and defends firmly.
This is delivered outside off from a shortish length. Dinesh Chandimal punches this to deep cover for a single.
Tossed up, around off. Theekshana prods and defends it.
Floats one up, on middle. Theekshana again lunges to defend it out.
Gets this to drift one, fuller and on leg. Theekshana keeps it out.
Full ball, way outside off. Chandimal pushes it to mid off.
Keeps it full and outside off. Chandimal works it to covers.
A low full toss, angling on the pads, flicked to deep square leg. No run taken.
A bouncer now on middle and leg. Chandimal lets it go over his head.
A length ball, outside off, hit to covers.
Bowls it very full and wide of off. Chandimal looks to drive but gets an inside edge and it takes a couple of bounces before it reaches to the keeper. That will be Tea on Day 1.
Ali serves a full ball on middle. Theekshana drives it to mid on.
Sliding down the leg side on a length. Theekshana tries to flick it away but misses. Rizwan appeals but the umpire is not interested.
Good shot from Theekshana! This is on a length and outside off. Theekshana punches off the front foot and through covers for three runs.
Length and on off. Chandimal taps it to point for one more.
Fuller ball on off. Theekshana defends it out.
Length and outside off, nips a bit away. Theekshana pushes off the outer half to point.
Seam from both ends then! Fuller and on middle. Chandimal on drives it to mid on.
FOUR! Poor delivery! Overpitched and outside off. Chandimal has ample time as he drives it hard and through covers for a boundary.
Length and on middle. Kept out.
Bangs a bouncer on middle. Chandimal sits under it.
Short one again, this time Chandimal pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
A full ball, tailing down the leg side. Theekshana looks to flick it but misses. Good take from the keeper. A stifled appeal follows too but Afridi shakes his head later.
On a length and outside off. Chandimal has a wild swing at it but misses.
Goes full now, outside off. Chandimal pushes it to covers.
Good running! A slower full ball on middle, Chandimal flicks it to deep square leg for a couple of runs. Theekshana was struggling to run across but makes in time.
Bouncer on middle. Left alone.

OUT! TAKEN! Pakistan get the big fish! This is full and outside off, width there too and it is there to be hit. Dinesh Chandimal tries to drive it hard and uppishly but Yasir Shah at covers dives to his right and takes a blinder to get rid of the Lankan batter. It was well across him but Shah got both hands on it. Superb catch. Dinesh Chandimal goes after a fine innings.
Howout: c Yasir Shah b Hasan Ali

Commentary: A yorker on middle. Rajitha digs it out to mid-wicket.
Bangs in a bouncer on middle, Maheesh Theekshana ducks under it.
Fullish delivery on middle and leg, Maheesh Theekshana flicks it through square leg for brace.
Full again outside off, Maheesh Theekshana plays a solid drive but straight to mid off.
FOUR! Timed really well. Shaheen Afridi bowls the slower ball on a length and on middle and leg. Maheesh Theekshana times it past the bowler's right towards the long on fence for a boundary.
FOUR! Nice shot! This is back of a length outside off, Maheesh Theekshana gets on top of it and just guides it past point for another boundary.
Goes full and on middle, Maheesh Theekshana blocks it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on off, Kasun Rajitha defends it back to Ali.
Full once again onto the pads, Kasun Rajitha tries work it through the leg side but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Sharp Bouncer! Hasan Ali bowls a well directed bouncer on middle and leg. Kasun Rajitha does well to take away his bat and ducks under it.
Good length in stump line, Kasun Rajitha uses his feet and fends it to the off side.
Goes for the yorker this time and lands it right on middle, Kasun Rajitha digs it out well.
Slower bouncer this time, around off. Kasun Rajitha offers no shot at it.
Back of a length delivery on off, nips back in sharply. Maheesh Theekshana is late to decide whether to leave it or not and gets hit on his right thumb.
Lands a short ball on middle and off, Maheesh Theekshana sits under it.
Pulls his length back again, Maheesh Theekshana taps it to point for a single.
This is full and outside off, Kasun Rajitha drives it past the mid off fielder. Yasir Shah gives chase and stops the ball just before the boundary and they get three runs.

Shaheen Afridi bowls it back of a length on off, angling in from 'round the wicket. Maheesh Theekshana tries to guide it through point but gets hit again on his right thumb. He is looking at it right now, maybe he is hurt a bit as it is his bowling hand.
Full and on middle, Kasun Rajitha knocks it to short leg.

Starts with a short ball outside off, shaping away. Maheesh Theekshana tries to guide it to third man but could not connect as the ball goes past the outside edge. There is a slight appeal but the finger stays down.
Full and on middle, Maheesh Theekshana drills it straight to mid on.
Full once again around off, Maheesh Theekshana works it towards mid off and gets across for a qucik single.
Hasan Ali serves it full and on middle, taking pace of it. Kasun Rajitha blocks it to short mid-wicket.
Full and wide around off, Kasun Rajitha plays a good looking drive thorugh covers for a brace.
Slower ball again, on a length and on off. Kasun Rajitha is into his shot early and gets hit on his body.
Yasir Shah starts with a nicely tossed up delivery on middle and leg, turning away. Maheesh Theekshana blocks it off well.
On middle, blocked out.
Floated around off, Maheesh Theekshana leans forward and defends it to the off side.
Tossed up again full around off, Maheesh Theekshana fends it away.
This is slower through the air, spinning away. Maheesh Theekshana strides forward to play it towards mid off but the ball takes a leading edge and rolls past point, They cross.
BEATEN! Top spinner this time from Shah around middle. Kasun Rajitha tries to block it from his front foot but gets beaten on his outside edge by the late turn.
Naseem Shah begins with a good length delivery outside off, Maheesh Theekshana knocks this towards cover.

Pulls his length back outside off, Maheesh Theekshana works this towards point. The fielder takes aim at the non-striker's end and hits the bat of Kasun Rajitha. Ricochets to the deep but they do not take a run. Good sportsmanship shown here by the Lankan batters.
This one is served short and wide from the stump, Maheesh Theekshana slashes at it and misses. He is disappointed in missing out there.
On a good length outside off, Maheesh Theekshana works this to mid on.
Naseem Shah bangs this in short outside off, Maheesh Theekshana ducks under this one.

FOUR! Sri Lanka reach the 200 run mark with that boundary! Poor bowling from Pakistan, as this is banged in short and wide from off stump, Maheesh Theekshana gets under this and works it over the gap at slips towards the third man fence to push Sri Lanka to a decent total.
Yasir Shah serves this full and angling down the pads, Kasun Rajitha clips this towards fine leg for a single.
Full delivery outside off, Maheesh Theekshana hits this straight to cover.
Full once again in line with the stumps, Maheesh Theekshana defends this towards the cover region.
A fraction short outside off, Maheesh Theekshana works this through mid-wicket for a single.
Full and pitching on leg, Kasun Rajitha fends this towards mid on.
Yasir Shah serves this full once again, Kasun Rajitha solid in defense as he plays this towards mid on.
On a good length outside off, Maheesh Theekshana defends this towards cover.
This is served on a good length and well outside off, Maheesh Theekshana knocks this firmly towards mid off.
Naseem Shah goes back of a length outside off, Maheesh Theekshana guides this towards third man for a single.
This one is on a good length and in line with the stumps, Kasun Rajitha fends it down towards short leg.

Kasun Rajitha gets this straight on the helmet! That looks like a bad hit! The physio has been called on immediately! Naseem Shah bangs it in short and aims it for the jugular. Kasun Rajitha tries to duck but is late to react and gets hit on the side of his head!
Naseem Shah delivers this on a good length angled into the pads, Kasun Rajitha clips it towards deep backward square leg for a couple of runs.
Yasir Shah flights this full on middle. Maheesh Theekshana defends this to the right of the bowler.

SIX! What a hit! Yasir Shah bowls this a fraction short outside off, Maheesh Theekshana shimmies down the wicket and reaches for the ball. Gets good connection as he lifts it over the mid off boundary for a biggie! Maheesh Theekshana is playing quite a cameo here!
Full outside off, Maheesh Theekshana reaches for it and drags it to mid on.
Flighted full outside off, Maheesh Theekshana guides this past point for a single.
Yasir Shah goes full once again on an off stump line, Kasun Rajitha looks to fend and gets a thick edge towards point. They rush across for a single and make it.
Beaten! Yasir Shah loops this full outside off, Maheesh Theekshana pushes for it and gets beaten by the sharp turn.
Naseem Shah bowls from 'round the wicket and he bangs this short but going down leg, Kasun Rajitha leaves this one alone.

DROPPED! Oh my! Pakistan have been looking for this wicket and Hasan Ali has made an absolute mess! The leg stump line almost worked for Pakistan as this is served back of a length. Kasun Rajitha looks to work this leg side and gets a top edge towards backward square leg. Hasan Ali places himself under the ball and just lets it go through his palms down on the ground! What a miss!
NO BALL! Lack of discipline from Pakistan here! Naseem Shah serves this on a good length angling towards off, Maheesh Theekshana works this through point for a single.

NO BALL! Back-to-back no balls! The bowler seems a little flustered here! Bowls this back of a length and on leg, Kasun Rajitha gets on his toes and defends solidly. Naseem Shah needs to measure his run up once again!
Naseem Shah continues bowling short and angling in from outside leg. Kasun Rajitha looks to leave and gets hit under his arm.
Back-of-a-length delivery angled into the body, Kasun Rajitha fends this towards short leg.
Naseem Shah is persisting with the short ball length angling in from outside leg, Kasun Rajitha tucks this towards backward square leg.
Back-of-a-length delivery into the batter. Kasun Rajitha stands tall and plays with soft hands as the ball falls into the surface.
Tossed up, on off. Theekshana drives it to long off for a single.
Full and on off, spinning sharply away. Rajitha prods to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
A floated ball outside off, pushed to covers.
Shorter and outside off. Rajitha punches it to mid off.
A googly, full and on middle. Rajitha leans and blocks it out.
FOUR! More runs for the Lankans! This is too full and sliding down the leg side. Rajitha sweeps it, not well but enough to make a connection and the ball races to the fine leg fence.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! A slower bouncer, on middle. Maheesh Theekshana tries to ramp it over the keeper but gets a faint edge and Mohammad Rizwan makes no mistake, and pouches it safely. Sri Lanka are all out on 222.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary: Starts with a fuller ball around off. Shafique pushes it to mid on.
FOUR! Pakistan and Abdullah Shafique are underway! A length ball, outside off. Shafique opens the face of the bat and dabs it past backward point for a boundary.
Five wides! Ohh! What was that! Rajitha certainly lost it! Full and way, way down the leg side, almost out of the pitch and no chance for the keeper to save it. It races into the fine leg fence.
On a length and outside off. Shafique drops it to covers.
This is full and outside off, makes it to move away. Shafique shoulders arms to it.
Pitched up on off, it is driven to mid off.
Short of a length and on off. Shafique defends on the back foot.
Starts with a fuller ball, outside off, turning away. Imam-ul-Haq guides it to backward point for a single.
Tossed up, drifting on middle. Shafique prods and inside edges his defense to short fine leg.
Quicker, fuller and on middle. Shafique leans and tucks it to square leg.
Slightly short and on middle, nudged to mid-wicket.
Flighted, full and around off. Shafique takes a step forward and blocks it out.
Too full and on middle, floats it up. Shafique whips it to square leg. Good start by Theekshana.
Full and outside off, at 139 clicks. Imam leaves it alone.
Lands it full and outside off. Imam carves it to the left of point for a single.
Angles it on the pads. Shafique tucks it to square leg.
On middle, eased down to mid on.
Pushes it full and outside off. Shafique works it to covers.
Lands it on a length and on top of off. Shafique makes a solid block.
Flights a slower ball, full and on off. Imam prods to defend but gets a thick outside edge to point. He is getting a bit of turn.
Sharp turn this time! Full and outside off, lands and spins away. Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone.

Edged but safe! A loopy ball, outside off, moving away. Imam-ul-Haq lunges to defend across but gets an outside edge, past second slip and to backward point. Sri Lanka have a backward short leg in place.
Flatter and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq punches it to point.
Slows it more and angles a fuller ball, outside off, Imam-ul-Haq shoulders arms to it.
Imam-ul-Haq takes it on the full and drives it to mid off. A maiden then for Maheesh Theekshana.
Fuller and outside off, nipping away. Shafique leans and pushes it through point for one more.
Very full, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq squeezes it out to point.
On a length and targeting the stumps. Imam-ul-Haq keeps it out.
Outside off, fuller, left alone.
Keeps it full and on middle. Imam-ul-Haq drives it back to the bowler.

Not out it is! A length ball, around off, it shoots and nips back in. Imam-ul-Haq tries to work it away but misses and gets pinged low on the thigh pad. A huge appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. Height might be the issue there but still Sri Lanka take the review. Ultra Edge shows no bat. Ball Tracking shows wickets missing. Sri Lanka burn their review.
Floated on middle, Abdullah Shafique blocks it back to the bowler.
Flatter around off, Abdullah Shafique knocks it onto the ground.
Slower through the air, turning in. Abdullah Shafique nudges it to square leg.
Flatter and quicker around off, Abdullah Shafique fends it to the off side.
Darts this one on middle, Abdullah Shafique tucks it to mid-wicket.
TURN AND BOUNCE! This is tossed up on middle, turning into the batter. Abdullah Shafique flicks it and the ball goes on the bounce to backward short leg.
Good length outside off, Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone.

OUT! LBW! Kasun Rajitha gets the breakthrough for Sri Lanka. He bowls it full around off, angling in towards the batter. Imam-ul-Haq goes for the drive but gets beaten by the movement. He gets rapped hard on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW and it is given. Imam-ul-Haq goes for the review. Ultra Edge and Ball Tracking shows nothing to change the decision. The impact was umpire's call while the wickets were hitting so he has to go. Pakistan lose their first wicket.
Howout: lbw b Kasun Rajitha

Commentary: Good-length delivery on off, shaping away. Azhar Ali lets it go to the keeper.
On a length around off, Azhar Ali pushes it towards point.
Kasun Rajitha is getting the ball to swing. This is full and on off, nipping away. Azhar Ali knocks it straight to point.
A wicket-maiden from Kasun Rajitha. He bowls it on a length and on middle, nips away slightly. Azhar Ali does well to block it to the off side.
Tossed up on middle and off, Abdullah Shafique defends it down the pitch.
Flighted delivery on middle, turning away sharply. Abdullah Shafique flicks it down to the ground and towards backward short leg.
Flighted full on middle, worked towards mid-wicket.
Full and angling into the pads, Abdullah Shafique nudges it to backward square leg.
Tossed up on middle. Shafique prods and blocks it out.
Keeps it full and on middle. Shafique solidly blocks it again.
Kasun Rajitha starts of with a good-length delivery just outside off, Azhar Ali taps this down the pitch to the right of the bowler.
On a good length once again, wider from off stump. Azhar Ali knocks this towards the cover fielder.
Bowls it full on middle, shaping away. Azhar Ali blocks it back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery around off, Azhar Ali covers his stumps and pushes this towards mid off.
Great bowling by Kasun Rajitha. He bowls it full again on middle, nipping away slightly. Azhar Ali fends it to covers.
A maiden over by Kasun Rajitha. This is on a length outside off, Azhar Ali gets in line of the ball and punches it to short covers.
FOUR! Abdullah Shafique looks to break the shackles. This is tossed up on middle, Abdullah Shafique uses his feet and just lofts it against the spin over mid-wicket for a boundary.
On middle, blocked out.
Darts this full and on the leg stump. Abdullah Shafique flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Azhar Ali gets off the mark in his 11th delivery. This is tossed up outside off, Azhar Ali goes on his back foot and pushes it to covers with soft hands. He picks up a single.
Full and on middle, Abdullah Shafique looks to flick it but gets an inside edge onto his pads. There is a slight appeal but the fingers stays down.
On middle, Abdullah Shafique fends it to the leg side.
Prabath Jayasuriya begins with a full delivery flighted on middle, Azhar Ali pushes this towards mid off.
Pulls his length back slightly and in line with the stumps, Azhar Ali goes back in his crease and plays it back to the bowler.
Full this time and in line with the stumps, Azhar Ali defends this on the front foot back to the bowler.
Full delivery angled into the pads. Clipped towards mid-wicket.
Beaten! What a ripper! Prabath Jayasuriya flights the full outside off, Azhar Ali feels for it and is beaten by the turn. Unplayable delivery from Prabath Jayasuriya!
Full and in line with the stumps, Azhar Ali guides this towards mid on.
Slightly short and on middle, Abdullah Shafique rocks back and works it towards mid-wicket.
Maheesh Theekshana goes full and angles this down leg, Abdullah Shafique looks to clip this leg side but finds the short leg fielder.
Full this time and angling into the pads, Abdullah Shafique clips this through mid-wicket for a single.
Slightly short once again and turning into the pads, Azhar Ali guides this to backward sqaure leg,
Full and on the pads, Azhar Ali works this to the short mid-wicket fielder.
Maheesh Theekshana tosses this one full as well on the pads, Azhar Ali finds the same fielder.
Prabath Jayasuriya goes full outside off, Abdullah Shafique knocks this to the mid off fielder.
Full once again, flighted outside off. Abdullah Shafique hits this hard to the cover fielder who dives and stops it to his right.
Prabath Jayasuriya goes full outside off, Abdullah Shafique looks to defend and gets a thickish edge towards point.
Full and pitching on off, Abdullah Shafique paddles this towards fine leg for a brace.
Prabath Jayasuriya goes back to bowling outside off, on a full length. Abdullah Shafique fends this towards cover.
Flights this one full outside off, Abdullah Shafique happy to defend this in the cover region.
Maheesh Theekshana flights this full on the pads, Azhar Ali taps this back to the right of the bowler.
Full once again angled into the pads, Azhar Ali clips this towards mid-wicket.
Even fuller, almost on a yorker length, and quicker in the air. Azhar Ali digs this out back to the bowler.
Goes outside off and full, Azhar Ali defends this solidly back to Maheesh Theekshana.
Maheesh Theekshana goes 'round the wicket now and angles this in from leg stump from a shorter length. Azhar Ali clips this awkwardly towards backward square leg.
Similar line angled into the pads, and bowled short. Azhar Ali taps this down towards short leg.

This one was really close! Prabath Jayasuriya goes a fraction full outside off, Abdullah Shafique plays for the turn and gets beaten on the inside edge as the ball keep its line. Some extra bounce on offer and the ball just goes over the stumps!

Beats him on the outside edge this time! Prabath Jayasuriya is bowling beautifully here as he serves this full outside off. Abdullah Shafique gets beaten by the turn this time as he pushes for it and the ball zips past his outside edge! What a delivery!
Abdullah Shafique shuffles down the wicket and catches the ball on the full. Hits it back to the bowler who stops it diving to his right.
Prabath Jayasuriya serves this full outside off and gets the ball to turn away, Abdullah Shafique goes on the backfoot and fends this down the pitch.

OUT! LBW! That is plumb in front of the wicket! Prabath Jayasuriya has bowled beautifully in this over and he is duly rewarded! Prabath Jayasuriya bowls this full on off, and it's been delivered a shade quicker. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend but plays the wrong line to this arm ball and gets hit straight on the pads. He considers taking the review, then decides against it. Good decision from Abdullah Shafique to just walk off the field as this was surely headed for the stumps!
Howout: lbw b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: UNPLAYABLE! Prabath Jayasuriya bowls this slower through the air, full and on middle, Babar Azam leans forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. Almost two in two for Prabath Jayasuriya. That ends a wonderful over as he registers a wicket maiden!
Full and on middle, blocked back to the bowler.
Full again on off, Azhar Ali knocks it to the off side.
Floated full on middle, Azhar Ali tucks it to mid-wicket.
Flatter delivery angled in, Azhar Ali is solid in his defense.
Tossed up outside off, Azhar Ali goes for the drive but gets a leading edge towards backward point. They cross.
Darts this one full on middle, Babar Azam digs it out onto the pitch.
Floated around off, Azhar Ali leans on and blocks it to silly mid off.
Tossed up on off, turning away, Azhar Ali leaves it alone.

EDGED BUT SAFE! This tossed up again on middle and off, turning away. Azhar Ali tries to defend it with soft hands but gets an outside edge. Luckily for him it does not carry to the second slip fielder.
Tossed up around off, spinning away. Azhar Ali offers no shot at it.
Full and on off, Azhar Ali dances down the track and drives it hard but straight to covers.
On middle, blocked out.
Babar Azam gets off the mark. This is a bit short around off, Babar Azam pushes it through covers for a single.
Full toss on middle and off, Azhar Ali drillis it towards long off for a run. He is not happy with himself as it was there to be punished.
Floated on middle and leg, Babar Azam tucks it to square leg.
Full on middle, Babar Azam knocks it to mid-wicket.
Full once again on the pads, Babar Azam flicks it to short leg.
Tossed up around off, spinning back in. Babar Azam blocks it from his back foot. That will be STUMPS ON DAY 1.

PUT DOWN! Ohh! What a start by Prabath Jayasuriya! Dimuth Karunaratne puts down a dolly! This is full and outside off. Ali pushes it away from the body and aerially. Dimuth Karunaratne is standing at covers and he dives forward to catch it but spills it down. Should have been taken. Prabath Jayasuriya continues from where he left off. Creating chances.
Flatter and on off. Ali blocks it off the back foot.

OUT! LBW! THREE REDS! What a start by Jayasuriya! Just the start the Lankan were hoping for! Jayasuriya serves a length ball, angling around middle and holds its line. Ali gets on his knee and looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads. Sri Lanka put up a huge appeal and the finger goes up. Ali chats with Azam and takes the review at the last second. A desperate one to be honest. Looks plumb there! No bat confirms Ultra Edge! Ball Tracking shows three reds and Ali has to walk back!
Howout: lbw b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: Flatter and on leg. Rizwan sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a single.
This one lands outside off and spins sharply away. Azam watchfully lets it go.
Nicely tossed up, full and on off. Azam prods and blocks it out.
A length ball, outside off and nips away a touch. Rizwan defends off the outer half to point. A no ball is given as Rajitha overstepped.
Fuller and on off. Rizwan stays back to block.
Angles it on the pads, it is flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Good start by Rajitha! This is full and outside off, jags a bit away. Azam waits and makes a late block.
FOUR! First boundary of Day 2! Little bit of width here, on a length. Azam punches off the back foot and through point for a boundary.
FOUR! Too easy for Babar! Slides one on the pads. Azam flicks it past mid-wicket and into vacant deep region for four more.
On a length and outside off. Azam shoulders arms to it.
FOUR! Pakistan are putting away the loose balls! An arm ball, too full and outside off. Rizwan smashes it through covers, no chance for the fielder to chase it. A boundary.
Tossed up on middle. Defended out.
A loopy ball, around off. Rizwan again blocks it.
Tossed up, full and outside off. Rizwan prods and defends it to silly point.
Too full from Jayasuriya! Should drag his length a bit back. This is on middle, defended.
Perfect length! Gives a bit of flight here, fuller and on off, gets the required turn as well. Rizwan is beaten as the ball trims past his defensive outside edge.
Too full and outside off, driven to covers.
Pushed through on leg, clipped to square leg.
Full and spinning into the batter, Azam tucks it past square leg for one more.
Quicker and fuller on off, eased down to mid on.
Quicker again, fuller and on middle. Rizwan whips it through mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up on off. Defended out.
Floated on off. Rizwan stays back to defend it.
Pitched up and outside off. Rizwan watchfully dead bats it.
Lands it full and around off. Rizwan leans and blocks it.
FOUR! Again this is too full and on middle. Rizwan plays a straight drive past the bowler for a boundary.
Slows it up now, on off. Rizwan prods and blocks it.
This is the arm ball, fraction short and on middle, it is nudged to mid-wicket.
Sri Lanka are lacking in accuracy! Shorter and on middle, Azam pulls it to the left of square leg for a single. Good stop there.
Much better! Probably the carrom ball, shorter and outside off. Rizwan stands tall and defends inside the line.
Goes full now on middle, Rizwan turns it to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on leg. Rizwan tickles it fine past short leg for one.
Two runs! Too short and outside off. Azam punches off the back foot through covers for a brace.
Fuller ball from around the wicket and on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Beauty! Slows this flighted ball ever so well, length and on off. Rizwan prods to defend but slight turn gets the outside edge to the right of first slip.
On middle, blocked out.
Overpitched and on off. Rizwan strides forward to block it.
Little bit of width, fuller and this is driven to covers.
Tosses it up, angling on middle. Rizwan defends on the off side.
Tight on the stumps. Rizwan is solid with his front foot defense.
Full and outside off, Babar Azam leans on and blocks it to the off side.
Floated on middle, blocked back to the bowler.
Full an on middle and leg, Babar Azam knocks it on the leg side.
Tossed up on middle, Babar Azam pushes it with his inner half past the short leg.
Too full and on middle, Babar Azam gets to the pitch of the ball and drills it to mid on for a quick single.
Floated on off, Mohammad Rizwan is solid in his defense.
Floated full on middle and leg, angling in. Babar Azam uses his feet and flicks it through square leg for a brace.
Slower through the air around off, turning away. Babar Azam offers no shot at it.
A bit short outside off, Babar Azam stays back and punches it past point for one.
Full and on middle and leg, Mohammad Rizwan goes down and sweeps it to deep square leg for one more.
Tossed up on off, Babar Azam defends it to the off side.
FOUR! Nicely played! This is short again outside off, Babar Azam cuts it well past point from his back foot for a boundary. 10000 International career runs for Babar Azam!
FOUR! Good start to the over. Maheesh Theekshana bowls a full toss on leg, Mohammad Rizwan paddles it fine towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Full and on middle, Mohammad Rizwan works it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Floated on middle, Babar Azam steps out and blocks it to mid-wicket.
Tries the carrom ball, down the leg. Babar Azam misses his flick.
Quicker and flatter this time on middle. Babar Azam defends it of his back foot.
Gives it some air on middle, turning in. Babar Azam pushes it to square leg.
Nicely tossed up on middle, turning away. Mohammad Rizwan knocks it to silly mid off.
Flatter on middle and leg, Mohammad Rizwan pushes it of his inner half towards square leg.
Full and around off, Mohammad Rizwan drives it through covers for one.
On middle, blocked out.
Slower through the air around off, turning away a bit. Babar Azam is early in his shot and knocks it past silly point.
Tossed up on off, Babar Azam leans forward and defends it to the off side.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Ramesh Mendis takes a wicket with the first ball of his spell. This is short and down the leg side, Mohammad Rizwan tries to flick it from his back foot but only manages a glove towards the keeper. Niroshan Dickwella takes a sharp catch moving to his left. Should have easily avoided but he goes for it. Rizwan walks back without even thinking to review it.
Howout: c Niroshan Dickwella b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary: FOUR BYES! This is full and sliding down the leg again, AghaSalman misses his flick and this time Niroshan Dickwella cannot stop it as well. The ball races towards the fine leg fence for four byes.
On middle, blocked out.
Agha Salman gets off the mark. This is darted on middle and leg, Agha Salman tucks it away to square leg for one.
Full and on off, Babar Azam comes forward and blocks it down the pitch.
Just Short! Ramesh Mendis tosses it on middle and leg, turning in. Babar Azam leans on to block but gets a thick edge and the ball just falls short of the short leg fielder.
Prabath Jayasuriya flights this one full outside off, Agha Salman looks to sweep and misses. Niroshan Dickwella whips the bails off and appeals for a stumping. The replay shows he is well in.
This one is flighted full on middle, Agha Salman gets a stride forward and defends towards short leg.
Shorter in length and angled into the pads, Agha Salman misses his clip as the ball thuds into his pads.
Prabath Jayasuriya tosses this full on middle, Agha Salman defends this back to the bowler.
Prabath Jayasuriya bowls this one full as well and in line with the stumps, Agha Salman pushes forward and gets an inside edge just away from short leg.
Prabath Jayasuriya tosses this one full outside off, Agha Salman gets a thickish outside edge towards gully.
Ramesh Mendis gets the ball to turn from outside off on a fuller length, Babar Azam strides forward and defends towards cover.
Sharp turn for Ramesh Mendis. Pitches this short outside off, Babar Azam goes back in the crease and gets cramped for space as he tries to defend.
Full outside off, Babar Azam fends this towards the cover fielder.
Shorter in length and turning down leg, Babar Azam leaves this one alone.
Full delivery angled into the stumps, Babar Azam knocks the ball back to the bowler's right.
Goes short this time and angles the ball into the pads, Babar Azam nudges it towards backward sqaure leg.
Prabath Jayasuriya serves this slower in the air, full and outside off, Agha Salman paddles this to short fine leg.
This is full and in line with the stumps, Agha Salman defends this back to the bowler.

FOUR! This is a release shot from Agha Salman! The pressure seemed to be building! Prabath Jayasuriya flights this full outside off, Agha Salman sweeps this from outside off over the short fine leg fielder for a boundary towards deep backward square leg. First boundary for Agha Salman in Test cricket.
Full delivery outside off, Agha Salman fends this towards the short cover fielder.
Slows it up on off. Salman gets forward only to block it out.

OUT! LBW! Massive appeal and the finger has been raised! Prabath Jayasuriya goes full around off and once again gets the ball to keep its line. Agha Salman looks to play for the turn and misses the ball as it goes on to hit the pads. The umpire says it is out and the batter decides to review this. There is no spike on Ultra Edge and Ball Tracker shows two reds and one umpires call as the ball goes onto clipping the top of leg stump. The on field decision stands and Pakistan have lost half their side!
Howout: lbw b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: Ramesh Mendis serves this full outside off, Babar Azam looks to stroke this offside and gets an inside edge towards mid-wicket.
Full outside off, Babar Azam gets across and clips it through mid-wicket for a single.
Pulls his length back a fraction, and serves this outside off, Mohammad Nawaz looks to slash this square of the wicket and misses.
Full and in line with the stumps, Mohammad Nawaz gets forward and defends this down the pitch.
Ramesh Mendis goes short outside off, Mohammad Nawaz goes back in the crease and punches it towards point to take a quick single.
This one is really full outside off, Babar Azam gets his front foot forward and smothers the ball into the pitch.
Full and angled into the pads from over the wicket. Mohammad Nawaz knocks this to the left of the bowler.
Prabath Jayasuriya serves this full once again on the pads, Mohammad Nawaz clips this towards long on for a single.
Goes 'round the wicket to the right-hander. Babar Azam looks to work the full delivery on middle towards mid-wicket but gets an inside edge towards deep backward point for a single.
This one is full outside off, Mohammad Nawaz fends this firmly towards cover.
Prabath Jayasuriya bowls a shade quicker and angles it into the pads from a fuller length. Mohammad Nawaz looks to fend this and gets a thick edge wide of short leg.
Full and spinning in from outside off, Mohammad Nawaz shuffles down to wicket to defend and negate the turn.
Tossed up on off. Azam leans and blocks it out.
Shorter and spinning way down the leg side. Azam shoulders arms to it.
Again this one is way down the leg side, spinning more away. Azam leaves it alone.
Mendis is getting a sharp turn here but could be better with his line! Shorter and on middle, it is pulled to deep square leg for a single.
Shorter, landing outside off and turning away. Nawaz slaps it to deep cover for one.
Tossed up, darting on the pads and turning away from the batter. Azam misses his flick.
Tossed up, spinning onto the pads. Nawaz lets it through and gets hit on the pads.
Touch short and on off. Nawaz skips down and dead bats it.
A loopy ball on middle, Nawaz sweeps it to deep square leg for a run.
FOUR! Not a good line here! Jayasuriya drops it short, slow and on off. Azam rocks back, stands tall and pulls it past mid-wicket for four. Classy from Azam.
Too full and on off. Kept out.

Not out it is! A loopy ball, slightly coming off the arm, around off. Azam prods across to defend but misses and gets pinged on the pads. A huge appeal for LBW but not given! Prabath Jayasuriya was convinced that it is very close and asks his skipper to take it upstairs. No bat there clearly. Ball Tracking shows the impact is umpire's call despite the wickets hitting. Talk about inches. Azam survives.
Beautiful delivery! This one lands around off, fuller and spins away. Nawaz is tempted forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Slightly shorter and outside off. Nawaz works it away but just to silly point.
A loopy ball on middle, swept to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller ball, angling on off. Azam uses his feet but doesn't reach to the pitch of the ball quite well, plays off the inner half and to mid-wicket.
On middle, kept out.
This one is spilled down the leg side, angled across. Azam leaves it alone.
A flighted ball, full and on off, steep bounce. Nawaz looks to sweep but gets hit high on the pads.
Nawaz waits back and plays it late to leg slip and the ball drops in front of the fielder.

OUT! TAKEN! Sharp catch by Oshada Fernando and Babar Azam watches another batter walk back! Beauty from Jayasuriya again! He gets his fourth wicket! Bowls a flatter ball, a bit quicker and slanting around middle and leg. Nawaz pre-meditates as he comes down the track and tries to flick it away but closes the face of the bat and it goes off the inner half of the bat and to short leg. Oshada Fernando had to show quick reflexes as he runs across to his right and takes it brilliantly. Might have lobed off his chest but he did well to hold onto it. Sri Lanka right on top.
Howout: c Oshada Fernando b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: OUT! LBW! Another one bites the dust! Shaheen Afridi stands there knowing nothing what happened and gets a nod from Azam that it is plumb in front. An arm ball from Jayasuriya, tossed up, fuller and around middle and off. Afridi clearly wasn't out there ready to play as he was too late to get his bat down to defend. Gets pinged on the back pad and the finger goes up after a massive appeal. Prabath Jayasuriya is on a Hat trick.
Howout: lbw b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: RIPPER! Missed the Hat trick by inches! What a bowler this man is! Tosses it up nicely, fuller and on off and it spins away. Shah gets beaten on the outside edge as he tries to defend.

ANOTHER RIPPER! What a delivery again! Jayasuriya keeps his line and length accurate as he bowls around off, there is more bounce this time and it misses the outside edge by inches as it brushes past it. There is a stifled appeal as well.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller and on off. Shah pushes it back to Mendis.
This one spins across sharply. Shah gets his pad in front as he tries to block it.
Tad short and on middle. Shah stays back and gets a bit of glove on it but falls safely on the leg side.
Tossed up on middle. Shah flicks it past square leg for one.
Too full and on off. Azam prods and makes a solid block.
Tossed up on off, Yasir Shah blocks it to the off side.
Full and on middle, angling in. Yasir Shah flicks it through mid-wicket for a comfortable three.
TURN AND BOUNCE! He bowls it a bit short on middle and off, turning away a bit too much. Babar Azam lets it go to the keeper.
On middle, blocked out.
Arm ball around off, spinning away, Babar Azam has a wild swing at it but could not connect. Niroshan Dickwella fails to gather it too and the batters get a bye run.
Tossed up on middle, Yasir Shah looks to block it but gets hit on his front pad. There is a slight appeal but the fingers stays down.
A bit short on middle, Babar Azam pulls it to deep square leg for one.
Floated on middle, spinning in. Yasir Shah misses his sweep and gets hit on his pads.
Flatter and quicker on middle and leg, Yasir Shah lets it hit the pads as it is going down the leg.
Tossed up around off, turning in sharply. Yasir Shah does well to block it out.
Full and on middle, Yasir Shah sweeps it hard and it deflects of the short leg fielder towards deep square leg. They cross.
A bit short on middle and leg, turning away. Babar Azam nudges it past leg gully for one.
Full and on off, this is pushed to mid off.
Floated on middle and leg, Babar Azam works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up on middle, Yasir Shah leans forward to block it out.
Floated outside off, Yasir Shah leaves it alone.
Flatter and quicker around off, this is pushed to covers.
Flighted delivery on off, Yasir Shah plays it gently towards point.
A bit short on middle, Babar Azam pulls it to deep square leg for a run.
Loopy delivery on off, Yasir Shah goes for the defense but gets an inside edge onto his pads and the ball goes just past short leg.
Floated on middle, Yasir Shah knocks it past short leg.
Tossed up on off, Yasir Shah comes down the track to whip it over mid on but misses it completely and gets hit on the pads.
Full and on middle, Yasir Shah drives it straight to mid on.
Shortish and on middle and leg, Yasir Shah tucks it through square leg for one.

That is a chance! Prabath Jayasuriya bowls this beautifully flighted full outside off, Yasir Shah goes to drive and gets a thick outside edge. Niroshan Dickwella gets gloves on this and takes the ball away from the slip fielder who is diving to his left. Goes to his right towards third man for a couple of runs. Had the keeper left that alone it would have been an easy catch for slip.
This is full outside off, Yasir Shah does not bother playing at it.
Full and in line with the stumps, Yasir Shah knocks this towards mid on.
Flighted full outside off, Yasir Shah defends this towards the cover fielder.
FOUR! Nice shot! Prabath Jayasuriya darts in the arm ball, angling down the leg. Yasir Shah reads it and drills it through mid-wicket for a boundary. 100 comes up for Pakistan.
Tossed up on off, Yasir Shah knocks it back to the bowler.
Fuller and sliding down the leg side. Azam lets it go.
Full and on middle, drilled down to long on for one.
Too full and on off, flicked to mid-wicket.
Full, floated and on the pads. Shah misses his flick. Good collect from the keeper.
Tosses it on off. Shah prods and blocks it.

DROPPED! Was a hard one as it needed something special! A low full toss on middle. Shah gets forward and sweeps it straight to short leg where Oshada Fernando had to get low to collect but he fails to hold on. He took one earlier but this one didn't stick. That will also be Lunch on Day 2.
Prabath Jayasuriya begins with a flighted delivery full outside off, Babar Azam fends this back to the bowler.
This one is tossed up full on middle, Babar Azam fends this off in the short leg region.
Similar delivery bowled full and in line with the stumps, Babar Azam nudges it towards short mid-wicket.
Continues bowling full on middle and leg, Babar Azam defends this down the pitch.
Full outside off, Babar Azam looks to stroke this through covers. Well stopped by the cover fielder.
Prabath Jayasuriya bowls this full and in line with the stumps. Babar Azam happy to fend this on his front foot back towards the bowler. Maiden to start of this session!
Maheesh Theekshana starts off with a full delivery outside off, Yasir Shah defends this back to the bowler.
Served full outside off, fended towards the cover fielder.
Full and wide outside off, Yasir Shah knocks this in the short cover region.
This one is flighted wide outside off on a fuller length. Yasir Shah looks to work this through covers and gets an outside edge to deep backward point for a brace.
Really full outside off stump, Yasir Shah taps this towards cover-point and takes a quick single.
This one angles around off and drifts away. Azam tries to play at it but misses.
Prabath Jayasuriya serves this full outside off and spinning away, Yasir Shah lifts his bat and lets it go.
Full once again just outside off, Yasir Shah fends this towards point.
Beaten! This one is served full and pitching on middle. Gets the ball to rip off the surface and beat the outside edge of Yasir Shah's bat as looks to work this leg side.
Served full outside off, Yasir Shah fends this back towards Prabath Jayasuriya.
This is full as well and pitching on an off stump line, Yasir Shah plays this back to the bowler as well.
Prabath Jayasuriya goes a fraction short and angling down leg, Yasir Shah clips this towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Full delivery outside off, Yasir Shah looks solid in defense as he plays this down towards cover.
Full delivery angled into the stumps, Yasir Shah clips it to short mid-wicket.
Too full on middle and leg, Yasir Shah tucks it through square leg for one.
Floated from 'round the wicket around middle, Babar Azam knocks it to short leg.
Full toss on middle and leg, Babar Azam works it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted delivery around off, turning away a bit. Yasir Shah goes for the forward defense but the ball takes a thick outside edge and roll towards point region. They cross.
BEAUTY! This is slower through the air on off, turning away. Yasir Shah tries to block it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full and on middle, Yasir Shah eases it to mid on.
Tossed up on off, Yasir Shah defends it to the off side.
Gives it some air on middle and off, turning away a bit too much. Yasir Shah puts a stride forward to defend but takes away his bat at the last moment. It goes to the keeper without doing any harm.
Full once again from Prabath Jayasuriya. This is pitching outside off and keeps is a straighter one. Gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Full once again angling into the pads, Yasir Shah nudges it towards backward square leg. Another maiden for Prabath Jayasuriya!
Goes 'round the wicket and fires this one full outside off, Babar Azam taps this back to the bowler.
Full and on the pads, Babar Azam clips this towards deep square leg for a single.
Maheesh Theekshana serves this full once again in line with the leg stump. Yasir Shah taps it to short leg.
Attacking the pads once again and bowled full, Yasir Shah works this towards short mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! This is smart bowling from Maheesh Theekshana! He has set up Yasir Shah beautifully! After consistently bowling a leg stump line, he fires a quick delivery full outside off. Yasir Shah reacts instinctively and looks to drive and gets a thick edge towards the slip fielder. Dhananjaya de Silva takes a sharp catch.
Howout: c Dhananjaya de Silva b Maheesh Theekshana

Commentary: Floated on middle and off, Hasan Ali pushes it towards cover with the outer half of his willow.
Nicely tossed up around off, again turning away a bit too much. Babar Azam leans on but decides not to play at it.
