Floated on off, Babar Azam knocks it towards silly mid off.
On middle, blocked back to the bowler.
Shortish and outside off, Babar Azam pushes it of his back foot through covers for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle and off, Hasan Ali defends it to silly mid off.
Too full this time around off, Hasan Ali drills it to long off for a run. He gets off the mark.
Maheesh Theekshana serves this full and in line with the stumps, Hasan Ali fends this back to the right of the bowler.
Goes 'round the wicket now, bowls this full and on middle and leg, Hasan Ali fends this back to the bolwer.
Full once again on off, Hasan Ali knocks this to the bowler's left.
This one is  a fraction short and angled into the pads, Hits the thigh pad, and lobs to short leg,
Maheesh Theekshana goes full on middle, Hasan Ali continues to defend on the front foot back down the pitch.

DROPPED! Tough chance but put down! Maheesh Theekshana flights this one full on middle, tempts the batter into going through with the shot. Hasan Ali hits this uppishly to the right of the bowler who reaches for it with both hands but only manages to parry it towards mid off. Maheesh Theekshana looks really disappointed and a chance goes begging!
Short and outside off, Babar Azam works this through point for a single.
Goes full now and just outside off, Hasan Ali defends this towards cover.
Flights this one full on middle, Hasan Ali sweeps this towards deep backward square leg and gets off strike.
Over the wicket now, bowls full and pitching on middle, Babar Azam defends this back to the bowler.
Prabath Jayasuriya goes short on middle and gets the ball turning towards the offside. Babar Azam goes back in the crease and punches it to deep cover for a single.
Full and outside off, Hasan Ali fends this down towards short cover.
FOUR! A freebie from Maheesh Theekshana. He bowls a full toss on off, Babar Azam drives it hard though extra cover for a easy boundary.
Tossed up on middle, Babar Azam blocks it onto the pitch.
Flatter and quicker around middle and leg, Babar Azam flicks it through mid-wicket for one.
A bit short on leg, Hasan Ali tries to nudge it on the leg side but could not connect well.
SIX! HUGE! This is flighted on middle and off, Hasan Ali goes down and slog-sweeps it over the deep square leg fence for a biggie.
SIX! Same shot, same result. This is full again on middle, Hasan Ali smashes it over deep square leg for another maximum. He is looking to take on the spinners now.
Darts this on middle, angling in. Babar Azam works it from his inner half towards the vacant fine leg region and picks up three runs.
Full and on middle, Hasan Ali  eases it to long on for a single.
Tossed up on off, blocked back to the bowler.
Too full on middle and leg, Babar Azam nudges it through square with soft hands and comes back for the second easily.
On middle, blocked out.

FIFTY! Babar Azam gets to his 22nd Test half-century and what a time to get it as well. This is floated on middle, Babar Azam steps out and works it to long on for a run. This has been a fighting knock and he has kept Pakistan still in the game. He will try to get close to the Sri Lankan total and reduce the deficit now.
Ramesh Mendis serves this a fraction short and turning down leg, Babar Azam leaves it alone.
This one is also a bit short and outside off, Babar Azam rocks back and defends down the pitch on his back foot.
Goes full this time and in line with the stumps, Babar Azam fends this back to the bowler.
Slightly short once again and outside off, Babar Azam covers the line and punches it to short mid on.
Ramesh Mendis flights this full outside off, Babar Azam taps this towards cover-point and rushes across for a single.
Flatter and angling down. Ali fends it to the right of leg slip.
Fuller and outside off, driven to sweeper cover for a single.
Drifts one full and outside off, eased to long off for one.
Slower, full and on middle. Blocked on front foot.
Flighted ball, on leg on fuller length. Azam bunts it with soft hands to short leg.
Slightly short and on off, Azam works it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up, outside off. Ali skips down and across to block it.
A loopy ball, tailing on leg, Azam hits it to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller and on middle. Ali smashes it to long on for one more.
Shorter, spinning across, down leg. Azam shoulders arms.
Floated, full and on off, turning in. Azam prods and bunts it to mid-wicket.
Goes quicker now on middle. Azam tucks it to deep square leg for a run.

OUT! TAKEN! Ali goes after playing a quick cameo! This is full and on middle, spinning in. It entices Ali to take on as he goes for the slog-sweep but fails to get the distance. Dinesh Chandimal at deep square leg gets under it and catches it. The wind was making the ball to swirl in the air but Chandimal hold onto it. Pakistan trail by 74 runs.
Howout: c Dinesh Chandimal b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary: Full and outside off, driven to covers.
On middle, blocked out.
Tossed up on middle. Azam lunges and defends.
Another solid front foot defense from Azam.
This is full and outside off. Azam drives it to covers where the fielder lets it through. A single. Shah has one ball to survive.
He survives! Flatter and outside off, it is punched to point.
Targets the stumps on middle. Defended out.
Pushed fuller and on middle. Azam defends it on the leg side.
Angles a full ball on off. Azam prods to defend but gets an inside edge in front of short leg.
Drifts one in around off. Kept out.
Tossed up, outside off. Azam tucks it to the right of the bowler. No run.
Azam gets a single! 150 up for Pakistan! This is full and quicker on off. Azam nudges it past the diving mid on fielder for a single.
Slows it up on middle. Azam strides forward to dead bat it.
Straight on off. Azam defends on the front foot.
So, Shah has three balls to survive! Too full and on middle, smashed to long on for one.
TURN AND BOUNCE! Tossed up on off. Shah prods to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. The keeper collects at a chest height.
Flighted and on off. Shah steps across and blocks it.
Sharp leave! This was the arm ball, quicker and too full, just outside off.  Shah shoulders arms to it.
Very full and on middle. Azam eases it to long on. No run taken.
Touch short and slanting on middle. Azam fends it to short leg.
A loopy ball, outside off, driven to long off for no run again.
Tossed up on middle. Azam flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Quicker, outside off. Shah gets his bat down to block it.
Flatter now on leg. Shah stays back and pushes it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, played back to the bowler.
Sliding around middle and leg. Kept out.
Fuller and around off. Azam lunges to block it.
Flatter and on middle. Azam rocks back and flicks it to deep mid-wicket. No run taken.
Shorter and outside off. Azam gets low and slaps it straight to the man at covers.
No run! Naseem will be on strike! Fuller and on off. Azam skips down and pushes it to mid off.

Not out! This is flighted on middle and off, turning away. Naseem Shah leans on to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. Niroshan Dickwella takes the bails off and there is an appeal for stumping. The umpire sends it upstairs. The replay shows that Shah got his foot down before the bails were dislodged. He survives.
On middle, blocked out.
Floated on off, Naseem Shah defends it to the off side.
Flighted on off, Naseem Shah again is solid in his defense.
This is pushed through on middle and leg, Naseem Shah blocks it from his back foot.

Not out! Maheesh Theekshana bowls this flatter and quicker on middle, Naseem Shah strides forward to block but gets beaten and get hits on his pads. The ball flies straight into the hands of short leg. They appeal for the catch and the finger goes up. Naseem Shah takes the review straightaway as he thinks there is no bat involved. The Ultra Edge confirms this and the on-field decision is changed to not out. Naseem Shah lives to fight another day.
Prabath Jayasuriya flights this full outside off, Babar Azam fends this back to the bowler.
Similar deliver flighted in, Babar Azam happy to knock this back to Prabath Jayasuriya.

Some sharp turn here and beats the outside edge! Lobbed full outside off, Babar Azam looks to push at it and gets beaten by the spin! Good ball from Prabath Jayasuriya but still not getting that edge.
Even fuller right at the pads, Babar Azam moves his leg away and plays it back to the bowler.
Prabath Jayasuriya flights this full outside off, Babar Azam gets an outside edge towards point and they take an easy single.
Naseem Shah negotiates the last ball well! Prabath Jayasuriya serves this full on off, Naseem Shah comes forward to defend solidly.
Kasun Rajitha begins with a full delivery outside off, Babar Azam drives this towards long off and refuses the single.

Kasun Rajitha delivers a slower ball, full and in line with the stumps, Babar Azam flicks this through square leg with soft hands and looks for a brace. There is no second here and Naseem Shah has four balls to face here in this over.

Kasun Rajitha serves a short delivery outside off, Naseem Shah ducks under this on slightly but is considerably high. Maybe Kasun Rajitha remembers the short ball Naseem Shah had bowled to hit him straight on the helmet!
Short once again outside off, Naseem Shah gets well on top of this and guides it towards wide second slip.
Kasun Rajitha goes 'round the wicket now and bowls this slightly back of a length. Delivers this outside leg and Naseem Shah opens his body to defend this back down the pitch in style.
Similar length and line, angled into the body. Naseem Shah defends this on the back foot.
Prabath Jayasuriya goes full on middle, can not get through Babar Azam's defense as he knocks it back to the bowler.
Short now and in line with the stumps, Babar Azam goes back in the crease and fends this back down the pitch.
Short and wide outside off, Babar Azam looks to cut and gets a thick edge towards deep backward point. Not interested in taking a single.
Prabath Jayasuriya delivers this full on off, Babar Azam takes a positive stride forward and fends the ball back down the pitch.
Full outside off this time, Babar Azam strokes this towards deep cover and take a single this time.
The fielders are placed around the batter. Prabath Jayasuriya flights this full outside off, Naseem Shah manages to defend this through all of them towards point.
Kasun Rajitha begins with a full delivery outside off, Babar Azam leaves this one alone.
Goes full again but a little closer to the off stump, Babar Azam defends this towards mid off.
Bangs this one in short outside off, Babar Azam pulls this towards deep square leg and wants to keep strike.
Full and angled in from outside off, Babar Azam flicks this towards deep mid-wicket and now decides to take a single.
Kasun Rajitha continues bowling short outside off to Naseem Shah. He sways out of the way to let it go through to the keeper.
After all the short balls, Kasun Rajitha resorts to a yorker right at the stumps. Naseem Shah gets his bat down in time and digs the ball out well.
Tossed up from 'round the wicket, Babar Azam pads it away.
Floated on leg, Babar Azam lets it hit him on the pads.
Flighted delivery around leg, Babar Azam agains pads it away.
Tossed up on middle, turning away sharply. Babar Azam tries to pad it but gets beaten and it goes through to the keeper.
Slightly short on the pads, Babar Azam works it through mid-wicket for a single. Naseem Shah has one ball to survive.
Naseem Shah survives. This is flighted on middle, Naseem Shah does well t block it out.
Full and on middle, angling in. Babar Azam flicks it to mid-wicket but denies the single.
Full again on middle, angling in. Babar Azam mistimes his drive towards long on.
Slower ball, full and down the leg. Babar Azam eases it towards long on.
Slower again on a yorker length and around off, hint of reverese swing there. Babar Azam drives it to long on and takes the single this time.
Bangs in a bouncer on middle and leg, Naseem Shah ducks underneath it.
Goes 'round the wicket and bowls a short ball on middle, angling away. Naseem Shah gets behind it and knocks it towards point.
Ramesh Mendis starts with a tossed up delivery around off, Babar Azam defends it to the leg side.
A bit short on middle, Babar Azam goes back and pulls it hard but it hits Oshada Fernando at short leg.
Floated on middle, Babar Azam pushes it past short leg, denies the single.
Tossed up on middle, turning in. Babar Azam nudges it to square leg.

A huge appeal for LBW but turned down. This is flighted outside off, turning in. Babar Azam looking at the field tries to heave it over mid-wicket but misses the ball and gets hit on his pads. The Sri Lankans appeal but the umpire is not interested. Dimuth Karunaratne decides to go for the review but Ball tracking shows that the impact and wickets both are umpires call so the on-field decision remains. In all of this the batters picked up one leg bye.
Tossed up on off, spinning in. Naseem Shah blocks it out.
Full toss on off, Babar Azam drives it long off.
Another full toss but this time on middle, Babar Azam drills it to long on, denies the single.
Fuller again sliding down the leg, Babar Azam flicks it through mid-wicket.
FOUR! HAMMERED! This is full again on off, Babar Azam smashes it past the non-striker towards the long on fence for a boundary. Naseem Shah showed good reflexes to get out of the way.
FOUR! Good shot! This is full again on middle, Babar Azam lofts it over mid-wicket for another boundary.
FOUR! Make that three in a row. Kasun Rajitha bowls another full delivery on off, Babar Azam plays the field and smears it over square leg for another boundary.
Full and on middle, Naseem Shah defends it well.
Flighted on off, Naseem Shah stays back and blocks it to the off side.
Full again on off, Naseem Shah is solid in his defense.
Flatter and quicker on leg, Naseem Shah works it to square leg.
Full on middle, Naseem Shah gets to the pitch and defends it onto the pitch.
Tossed up on off, Naseem Shah knocks it to silly mid off.
Short and down the leg, Babar Azam goes down and pulls it to backward square leg.
Full and on middle and leg, Babar Azam flicks it to mid-wicket.
Slower through the air on middle, turning down the leg. Babar Azam misses his flick.

An appeal for caught behind but turned down. Ramesh Mendis gives some air to this on middle, turning in sharply. Babar Azam misses his flick again. Niroshan Dickwella appeals for the catch but the finger stays down. Dimuth Karunaratne goes for the review but the Ultra Edge shows nothing and the on-field call remains.
Too full and on middle. Azam drills it to the right of the bowler.
Too short and on middle, Azam pulls it to deep square leg for a single. It should be Tea time but the play is extended by 30 minutes or so.
Prabath Jayasuriya goes over the wicket and bowls outside leg stump. This is full and turning into the pads. Babar Azam does not play at this.
This is closer to leg stump and full. Hits the pads and there is a stifled appeal. Clearly pitching outside leg.
Flights this full on the stumps. Babar Azam fends this back down the pitch.
This one is turning onto the pads from outside leg and a fraction short. Babar Azam nudges it through square leg for a single.
Goes 'round the wicket and attacks the stumps from a full length. Naseem Shah fends this down towards short leg.
On middle, blocked out.
Full delivery outside leg and spinning further away. Babar Azam leaves it alone.
Full and spinning into the pads from a leg stump line, Babar Azam flicks this towards mid-wicket.
Similar delivery, and Babar Azam plays the same shot and continues to retain strike.
Full delivery on the pads, The flick through deep mid-wicket gets him a single this time around.
Full and angled into the stumps. Naseem Shah showing a great exhibition of defensive shots.
Dhananjaya de Silva goes short and in line with the stumps, Naseem Shah goes deeper in the crease and fends it down the pitch.
Full and just outside off, Babar Azam defends this back to the bowler.
Tosses this one a fraction wider outside off on a full length. Babar Azam gets a huge stride forward and defends it to Prabath Jayasuriya.
Takes the length back, and bowls this shorter. Pitching in line with the stumps and Babar Azam goes back to play this on the back foot.
Tossed up on off, Babar Azam blocks it to the off side.
Goes over the wicket now and decides to bowl this full outside leg, Babar Azam defends this down the pitch.
Babar Azam gets the single he wanted. This is full and on off, Babar Azam guides it to long off for a single.
Dhananjaya de Silva bowls this full and down leg side, Turns away further and Babar Azam leaves it alone.
Pitching on leg and full, Babar Azam gets forward in defense.
Flighted full on the pads, Babar Azam taps this towards short leg.
This one is slightly short on the pads, Babar Azam uses the crease and flicks it towards short leg once again.
Full outside leg, Babar Azam gets his foot out of the way and defends it back to the bowler.

This is brilliant batting from Babar Azam as he gets down to a full delivery on leg and works it with soft hands towards cover for a quick single to keep strike. Sri Lanka need to get their fielders tight as they concede these singles on the last ball pretty easily.
Tossed up, angling on leg, defended out.
Shorter and outside off. Azam slaps it to deep point for no run.
Tosses it up, full and on middle. Azam prods and blocks it.
Fuller again on off. Azam lunges to defend it.
Slower, full and hint of away spin here. Azam leans and drives it to deep point for a single.
An arm ball, this one lands on off. Shah leans to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Nearly there but Naseem survives another over.
Too full on off. Azam pushes it back to the bowler.
SIX! KABOOM! Too short this on off. Azam clears his front leg and pulls it hard over cow corner for a biggie.
Another short one sliding down. Azam pulls it to deep square leg but does not take a single.
Azam moves into the 90s! Shorter and outside off, cut to deep backward point for a single.
On off, Shah pushes it to point.
Flatter and around off, stays a bit low. Shah gets low to block it.
GIves too much flight on off, whipped to deep mid-wicket for no run.
Foated, quicker and on off. Azam eases it to mid-wicket. Again no run.
This one comes with the arm, around off. Azam punches off the back foot to Jayasuriya.
Flatter and outside off, punched to covers.
A bit slower now, outside off. Azam pushes it to covers.
FOUR! Azam gets a boundary but Naseem will be on strike next over! A loopy ball, outside off. Azam goes inside out over covers for a boundary. He is on 94.
Very full and outside off. Shah jams it out to covers.

FOUR! Naseem Shah is off the mark on his 39th delivery! He raises his bat on the occasion! An unfortunate one though! This is full and angling on off. Shah looks to defend but gets an outside edge, past the diving second slip fielder and to the third man fence.
Touch fuller and on middle. Shah defends it out.
Attempts an inswinger but slides it on the pads, it is flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller ball on off, pushed to long off for a single. Can Shah survive one ball before Tea?

A bouncer, outside off and Shah doesn't attempt to play at it. That will be Tea on Day 2. Sri Lanka will love this break, it will break Pakistan's momentum and give a thought to how to break this last stand.
Tossed up on middle. Azam flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Azam moves to 99! A full toss on middle. Azam smashes it between long on and deep mid-wicket for a boundary. The stand moves to 50 as well.

HUNDRED FOR BABAR AZAM! His 7th in Test cricket! While all other batters struggled, this man is playing with sheer confidence! Deserves all the credit and applause he is getting at Galle! This is on the pads, it is flicked behind square on the leg side for one. He removes his helmet and soaks in all the applause.
Flatter and outside off, punched to second slip, who collects on a bounce.
On off, kept out.
Tossed up, full and outside off, it spins in sharply. Shah looks to push but gets a fain inside edge there.
Tossed up on middle, Babar Azam blocks it onto the leg side.
Flighted on middle and leg, Babar Azam plays it back to the bowler.
FOUR! This is full and on middle, Babar Azam goes down and smacks it through square leg for a boundary. 200 up for Pakistan.
Full again onto the pads, Babar Azam sweeps it easily towards deep mid-wicket but denies the single.
A bit short outside off, Babar Azam pushes it to covers and get across for a quick single.
Tossed up on off, Naseem Shah keeps it out well.
Flighted on middle, Babar Azam leans on and blocks it down the pitch.
Slightly shorter and outsdie off, Babar Azam cuts it towards the vacant third man area and picks up a brace.
Full and on leg, Babar Azam drives it past mid on but refuese the single.
Tossed up on middle, Babar Azam blocks it back to the bowler.
Flatter and quciker on the pads, Babar Azam helps it towards fine leg for one. Naseem Shah has one ball to survive.
Tossed up on off, Naseem Shah knocks it to silly mid off. He seems unbreakable at the moment.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Babar Azam uses his feet and knocks it to the leg side with the inner half of his blade.
Flighted on middle and off, Babar Azam gets to the pitch and plays it back to the bowler.
Full and on middle,  Babar Azam comes down the track and digs it towards mid-icket.
Full again on middle and leg, Babar Azam powers it to long on for a single.
A bit short outside off, Naseem Shah punches it of his back foot to short covers.
Loopy delivery on off, Naseem Shah blocks it towards silly point.
PEACH! This is tossed up on off, turning way sharply. Babar Azam strides forward to block but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full and on off, Babar Azam pushes this to covers.
What a delivery! Maheesh Theekshana bowls this slower through the air on off, holds its line. Babar Azam plays for the turn and gets beaten again on his outside edge.
A bit short around off, Babar Azam punches it through point for one.
Short again outside off, turning in. Naseem Shah blocks it to the off side.
Flighted on middle, Naseem Shah defends it well.
Tossed up on middle, Babar Azam defends it back to the bowler.
SIX! HUGE! This is tossed up on off, Babar Azam dances down the track and heaves it over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie. They trail by just 7 runs now.
Full and on off, Babar Azam goes for the drive but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
On middle, blocked out.
Full and on off, Babar Azam easily pushes it towards the vacant cover-point region for another single. Sri Lanka needs to stop giving these easy singles to Babar Azam.
Flatter and outside off, Naseem Shah lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery outside off, Babar Azam hit this through cover and this is good running to pick up a couple of runs.
Maheesh Theekshana goes full once again on middle, Babar Azam fends this back to the bowler.
Serves this really full outside off, Babar Azam digs it back out to Maheesh Theekshana.
Full once again and in line with the stumps, Babar Azam comes forward and smothers this into the pitch.

OUT! LBW! That is plumb! Babar Azam finally departs and his long vigil comes to an end! Maheesh Theekshana serves this slightly full and turning from outside off towards the stumps, Babar Azam looks to work this through square leg in the quest to rotate strike. Misses the line of the ball and gets hit on the pads right in front of the wicket. Pakistan have two reviews in their kitty and opts for it. No bat and three reds confirms the technology and the third umpire confirms it is out and asks the on-field umpire to stay with his decision! What an innings this has been from Babar Azam! An absolute pleasure to watch and its a shame it comes to an end!
Howout: lbw b Maheesh Theekshana

Commentary: Shaheen Afridi starts with length delivery outside off, angling away. Oshada Fernando lets it go to the keeper.
Goes full this time on off, Oshada Fernando pushes this in front of point and gets across for a quick single.
FOUR! Not a good delivery from Shaheen Afridi! He angles this down leg side and full, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks this towards fine leg to get off the mark with a boundary!
This is served on a good length outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne pushes at it and gets a thickish edge towards deep backward point for a single.
Full and angling away from outside off, Oshada Fernando is happy to leave this one alone.
This one is even wider from a good length. Oshada Fernando leaves this for the keeper to collect. 5 runs of the first over!
Mohammad Nawaz serves this full outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne gets down the wicket and looks to work this leg side. Gets hit on the pads and the players appeal. The impact seems to be outside off.
Sharp turn for the bowler. Serves this short and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne looks to cut this but the turn cramps him for space.
This is full and angled into the pads, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks this towards mid-wicket.
Full once again and pitching on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne works this to long on for a single.
Mohammad Nawaz continues bowling full and angles this into the pads, Oshada Fernando works this towards mid-wicket.
Mohammad Nawaz flights this one full and in line with the stumps. Oshada Fernando defends this solidly back to the bowler.
Shaheen Afridi serves this back of a length outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne guides this to deep backward point for a single.
This is full and angled into the pads, Oshada Fernando plays this firmly towards mid-wicket.
Shaheen Afridi goes wide outside off from a good length, Oshada Fernando leaves this one alone.
Pulls his length back a fraction, and delivers this on an off stump line. Oshada Fernando taps this towards cover-point and rushes across for a single.

FOUR! Good looking shot from Dimuth Karunaratne! Shaheen Afridi serves this full just outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne punches this straight back past the bowler who does get a hand to it. Slows the ball down but still manages to beat the mid off fielder and reach the long off fence for a boundary!
This is on a good length outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne watches this one closely as he leaves it alone.
Mohammad Nawaz goes full outside off, Oshada Fernando works this to mid off and takes a single as he sees the fielder on his heels.
Full once again outside off, gets the ball to turn into the pads, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks this towards mid-wicket.
This is full outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne gets across the stumps and fends this back towards the bowler.

Mohammad Nawaz goes full again and gets the ball to spin into the pads, Dimuth Karunaratne looks to flick this leg side and hits the short leg fielder. The ball seemed to be straight off the bat and would have been a difficult catch.
This is flighted full on off, Dimuth Karunaratne clips this towards mid-wicket once again.
Dimuth Karunaratne comes down the wicket and catches the ball on the full. Hits it back down the pitch and Mohammad Nawaz dives to his left to stop the ball.

FOUR! Streaky boundary but they all count! Shaheen Afridi serves this on a lovely length and gets the ball to shape away from the batter. Oshada Fernando looks to defend this straight and gets a thick outside edge between second slip and gully for a boundary to third man. Sri Lanka will be hoping this luck starts flowing their way!
Slightly short and outside off, Oshada Fernando looks to defend and the shape in beats his defense and hits his thigh pad.
Gets the outside edge once again. Shaheen Afridi serves this on a good length and angling away from the right-hander. Oshada Fernando looks to fend and gets a thick edge towards backward point.
Shaheen Afridi bowls this a slightly back-of-a-length and just outside off. Oshada Fernando looks to come forward and defend. The ball nips back in and gets an inside edge onto his pads.
This one is short and angling down leg, Oshada Fernando looks to pull and misses as the ball goes through to the keeper.
Full delivery just outside off, Oshada Fernando knocks this straight to mid off.
Tossed up on off. Karunaratne uses his feet to block it out.
A loopy ball on middle. Karunaratne skips down and eases it to long on for one more.
Short and outside off, cut but straight to point.
Flighted one, too full and on leg. Oshada Fernando whips it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Good shot! Floats one full and down the leg side. Oshada Fernando comes down the track and flicks it past mid-wicket and it races into the fence.
On middle, blocked out.
Fuller and outside off, it is driven hard but straight to cover.
An in-nipper, around off. Karunaratne hangs back and tucks it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, punched to covers.
Angles a length ball on the pads. Karunaratne fails to flick and gets hit on the right side of the front pad. An appeal but going down.
Outside off, a bouncer, left alone.
On a length and on off.  Karunaratne steps down and across to block it.
Salman on his debut, starts with a flatter ball spinning down the leg side. Oshada Fernando shoulders arms.
On middle, tucked to short leg with soft hands.
Tries a quicker one but spills it down the leg side. Oshada Fernando lets it through to the keeper.
Fuller and on middle. Oshada Fernando skips down and nudges it to mid-wicket.
Too short this time, quicker and going down. Oshada Fernando misses his pull shot.
This one goes straight with the arm, shorter and outside off. Oshada Fernando fails to cut it away. Agha Salman is getting good bounce as the keeper collects it near his chest.
Around off, fuller and Karunaratne plays it to long on as he comes down the track. One.
Shorter and outside off, it holds in the surface. Oshada Fernando is a bit late as he looks to cut, bottom edges it to the keeper.
Perfect line and length! Angles a full ball on off and makes it to spin away. Oshada Fernando is brought forward to defend but he misses.
Flatter and outside off, punched through covers for a single.
This is full and outside off. Karunaratne comes down the pitch and drags it to silly mid on.

Good work by Naseem! This is full and outside off. Karunaratne reverse sweeps it to deep point where Naseem Shah runs to his right and cuts it out. Two. He stops it with his leg and looks a bit injured. He walks off the field.
On middle, eased down to long on for one.
Angling on the pads, Karunaratne whacks it to square leg on the leg side for one.
Slides one down the leg side, fuller. Oshada Fernando gets his back leg to blast it out.
Full and on off, blocked out.
FOUR! Well played! Flighted, full and slanting on leg. Oshada Fernando sweeps it hard and through square leg for four.
A huge appeal for LBW but the impact might be outside off! Floats one full and outside off, angling in. Oshada Fernando tries to play the reverse sweep but misses and gets stung on the front pad.
Floated on off, Dimuth Karunaratne steps out to flick it but get an inside edge onto his pads and ball goes to short leg.
Full on off, Dimuth Karunaratne knocks it straight to silly mid on.

OUT! LBW! Mohammad Nawaz strikes. This is quicker and flatter around off, turning in. Dimuth Karunaratne is caught in his crease as he tries to flick and misses. He plays down the wrong line and gets hit on the pads in front of the stumps. There is an appeal for LBW and after some thought the umpire raises his finger. Dimuth Karunaratne takes the review. UltraEdge shows no bat involved and Ball Tracking shows two reds and just clipping the leg stump which is umpire's call. The on field decision stands and Sri Lanka lose their first wicket! Pakistan claim first blood and it is the all important wicket of the Sri Lankan skipper!
Howout: lbw b Mohammad Nawaz

Commentary: BEATEN! This is tossed up on middle and off, turning away. Kasun Rajitha leans on to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Flatter and quciker on middle, Kasun Rajitha flicks it of his inner blade through square leg for one.
RIPPER! Great bowling by Nawaz. This is again tossed up on middle, turning away. Oshada Fernando gets forward but is beaten on the outside edge.
Full and on off, Kasun Rajitha drives it to mid off.
Tossed up on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Full again on off, Kasun Rajitha drives it through covers for a brace.
Slightly short around off, Kasun Rajitha guides it to point.
Tossed up full on off, Kasun Rajitha drills it straight to mid off. The umpires have called for STUMPS on Day 2 due to bad light.
EDGED AND FOUR! Agha Salman bowls this full and around off, Kasun Rajitha tries to dig it out but gets a thick outside edge and the ball goes past the 1st slip and races away to the third man fence.
Full and on off, Oshada Fernando blocks it to the off side.
Full again and drifting into the pads, Oshada Fernando flicks it through square leg for one.
Full delivery and turning away from outside off, Kasun Rajitha pushes at it and misses.
Tossed up on off, turning away a bit too much. Kasun Rajitha makes an easy leave.
Floated on middle, defended onto the pitch.

OUT! LBW! The vigil of the nightwatchman ends early! Mohammad Nawaz serves this full and just outside off, and gets the ball to straighten after pitching. Kasun Rajitha plays the wrong line and gets hit low on the pads. The umpire has no hesitation to lift his finger as this is plumb in front of the wicket. Kasun Rajitha does not even think of a review as he walks back.
Howout: lbw b Mohammad Nawaz

Commentary: Shaheen Afridi starts from 'round the wicket and bowls it on a length outside off, angling away. Oshada Fernando leans on and plays a front foot defense towards short covers.
Full and on middle, Oshada Fernando blocks back to the bowler.
Full again around off, Oshada Fernando drives it through covers for a couple of runs.
Pulls his length back a bit around off, shaping away. Oshada Fernando knocks it to the off side.
Serves it full and on middle and leg, Oshada Fernando flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Full again on middle, Oshada Fernando blocks it back to the bowler.
Mohammad Nawaz starts off with a shorter one outside off, Kusal Mendis uses his wrists and clips the ball through mid-wicket for a brace.
This is full and in line with the stumps. Kusal Mendis defends this back down the pitch.
Big turn from outside off. Mohammad Nawaz serves this on full as well outside off, Kusal Mendis looks to defend and gets beaten.
This is flighted full and outside off, Kusal Mendis comes forward and fends it towards silly point.
Mohammad Nawaz goes a fraction shorter and gets the ball to come in with the arm into the stumps, Kusal Mendis gets back in his crease and manages to keep the ball out towards cover.
Serves this slightly short as well, and on off, Kusal Mendis guides this to the right of mid on for a single.
Good length on off, angling away. Kusal Mendis guides it to point.
On a length and on off, Kusal Mendis opens the face of his bat and knocks it towards point again.
Shaheen Afridi bowls it full and outside off, shaping further away. Kusal Mendis lifts his bat and lets it go to the keeper.
Pulls his length back a bit around off, angling away. Kusal Mendis leaves it alone.
Good line and length by Shaheen Afridi here. This is on a length and on middle and off. Kusal Mendis pushes it back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery on off, shaping away again. Kusal Mendis makes an easy leave. Shaheen Afridi needs to make the batsman play to cause any trouble.
Mohammad Nawaz begins this over with a short delivery wide outside off, Oshada Fernando gets back in his crease and cuts it through point for a couple of runs.
This is full and angling into the pads, Oshada Fernando clips this towards fine leg for a single.
Goes back to bowling a fraction short outside off, Kusal Mendis nudges this through mid-wicket for a single.
Served full and angling into the pads, Oshada Fernando taps it towards short leg.

Mohammad Nawaz pulls his length back once more and serves this well outside off, Oshada Fernando uses the depth of the crease and cut the ball late to the right of slip towards the third man for two more runs.
Bowls this full and quicker, angled into the stumps, Oshada Fernando clips it towards short mid-wicket.
Shaheen Afridi goes 'round the wicket and bowls it full, angling in. Kusal Mendis defends it back to the bowler.
Pulls is length back a bit on off, Kusal Mendis knocks this one to short covers.
Too full this time around off, Kusal Mendis drives it firmly but straight to mid off.
On a length and on off, shaping in. Kusal Mendis goes on his back foot and punches it onto the ground towards silly mid off.
Goes full and angled this into the stumps, Kusal Mendis fends this firmly back to the bowler.

On a good length outside off, Kusal Mendis puts a solid stride forward to defend this towards cover-point. Just a gentle tap that beats the fielder and runs towards the boundary as the batters complete three runs. Great timing on that defensive shot!
FOUR! Mohammad Nawaz has been slightly short and wide in this spell. This one is the same as Kusal Mendis goes on his back foot and cuts it late through backward point for a wonderful boundary!
Full delivery quicker in the air, Kusal Mendis goes back in the crease and taps it towards forward short leg.
Full and in line with the stumps, Fended back to the bowler.
Short once again outside off, Kusal Mendis cuts this one as well but finds the point fielder this time.
Mohammad Nawaz serves this full and on middle and off, Kusal Mendis knocks this back down the pitch.
This one is short and on off, Kusal Mendis goes on the back foot and dabs it towards cover.
Yasir Shah starts wirh a flatter dlivery on off, Oshada Fernando drives it to mid off.
Floated on off, Oshada Fernando drills it to the left of mid off and picks up a single this time.
Full again on off, Kusal Mendis pushes it hard to short covers.
Tossd up full on middle and off, Kusal Mendis makes room and drives it hard but only to find the short cover fielder again.
Floated on middle and leg, Kusal Mendis knocks it to short leg.
Tossed up full on off, Kusal Mendis blocks it to the off side.
That is a ripper! Mohammad Nawaz flights this full outside off, Oshada Fernando pushes at it and gets beaten b
Too full this time, outside off. Fernando leans and blocks it.
Slows it up, full and on off. Fernando lunges and blocks it out.
FOUR! Floats one full and outside off, extra bounce and spins away. Fernando tries to defend across and players off the outer half, past first slip and to the third man fence.
On middle, kept out.
Good line but Fernando is hard on his front foot defense. This is full and on middle. Defended.
Sharp turn again! Shorter and outside off, turning away. Mendis dabs with soft hands through third man for a couple of runs.
Tossed up on middle, Mendis defends on the front foot.
Pitches it up, around off, it is driven to covers for a single.
Angles a fuller ball on middle and makes it to spin away. Fernando stays back and defends it very late.
SIX! That is a superb shot! Tossed up, fuller and on off, leggie. Fernando pre-meditates and comes down the track, lofts it straight down for a biggie.
Flatter and outside off. Fernando hits it to covers. The spinners need to be more disciplined with their lines and slow a bit up. This is easy for the Lankans to rotate the strike and build momentum.
Width given, outside off, it is punched through covers for one.
Two runs! Cheeky! Too full and on off. Fernando sweeps it fine to fine leg for a brace.
Touch short and outside off, cut to point.
Slides one full and on off. Fernando again sweeps it to fine leg and collects a couple.
Much better from Nawaz! Slows this up, it is on a length and around off, skids off the surface. Fernando looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge, past first slip for a single.
Ends the over with a beautiful delivery! Again this straightens up off the surface, tossed up outside off. Mendis gets on the front foot but defends inside the line.
On a length and on off, Fernando steps down and fends it to mid-wicket.
Fuller ball, outside off, hint of away shape. Fernando defends off the outer half and to the gully region.
Tries to again shape back in but spills it down the leg side. Fernando misses his flick.
Outside off on a length. Blocked out.
On middle, nudged to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, nips back in around off. Fernando punches off the back foot to the man at extra cover.
Flatter and around off. Mendis rocks back and keeps it out on the off side.
FOUR! Shah gets a good amount of spins but the line is on leg, fuller and Mendis is quick to sweep this away through square leg for a boundary.
Shorter and outside off, too much width on offer. Mendis taps it to covers.
Flights it up, too full on middle. Blocked back to the bowler.
Around off, Mendis tucks it past mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
A googly, this is full and around off. Mendis prods and blocks it.
Hasan Ali serves this full outside off, Oshada Fernando fends this towards mid off.

FOUR! That is some ordinary fielding by Mohammad Nawaz! This is served on a good length outside off, Oshada Fernando guides this towards point. The fielder does not have his eye on the ball as he misses it and it goes towards the deep backward point boundary for four runs!
On a good length outside off, Oshada Fernando taps this towards the cover fielder.
Hasan Ali serves this slightly back of a length outside off, Oshada Fernando slashes this towards point.
Full delivery outside off and angling into the batter, Oshada Fernando fends this back to the bowler who feigns a throw back at the stumps.
This one is full as well outside off, Oshada Fernando hits this firmly but finds the cover fielder!
Yasir Shah begins with a shorter delivery drifting into the pads, Kusal Mendis nudges this towards backward square leg for a single.
Flights this full outside off, Oshada Fernando gets a stride forward and fends this down the pitch.

FOUR! Lovely use of the feet by Oshada Fernando! This is full outside off, Oshada Fernando charges down the wicket and punches the ball straight back to the left of the bowler. This is hit really hard and the ball flies to the long off fence for a boundary!

Brings up a beautifully constructed half-century! Yasir Shah serves this full on the pads, Oshada Fernando clips it through backward square leg for a single. Sri Lanka will hope Oshada Fernando continues batting for long as a lot of work has to be done here!
Yasir Shah serves this short and wide from off stump. Kusal Mendis cuts this hard and finds the point fielder.
Flights this full and drifting into the pads, Oshada Fernando clears his front foot and hits it straight to mid on.
This is served on a good length and in line with the off stump, Kusal Mendis defends this back down the pitch.
Hasan Ali goes straight on a good length, Kusal Mendis clips this towards deep backward square leg for a couple of runs.
This is on a good length outside off, Kusal Mendis dabs this towards gully.
This is outside off from a good length. Kusal Mendis raises his hands and lets this one through.

FOUR! That is another lucky boundary for Sri Lanka this morning! Hasan Ali serves this on a lovely length outside off, Kusal Mendis looks to stroke this but gets a thick outside edge past the slip codron for a boundary! That brings up 100 for Sri Lanka and they are putting up a good show second time around!
This is on a good length outside off, Kusal Mendis leaves this one alone.

An appeal for caught behind but turned down. This is tossed up on middle and off, turning away sharply. Oshada Fernando leans forward to block but gets beaten on the outside edge. Mohammad Rizwan appeal for the catch but the finger stays down. He covinces the skipper to take the review but Ultra Edge shows there is no bat involved. A really poor review. There was a big gap there.
Floated on middle, turning away a bit. Oshada Fernando tucks it to mid on.
Full and on middle, Oshada Fernando sweeps it to deep square leg for one.
Flighted delivery on off, Kusal Mendis uses his feet and pushes it to covers for a single.
Tossed up on middle and off, Oshada Fernando knocks it to covers.
This is almost on a yorker length and on off, Oshada Fernando digs it to long off for one more.
Back of a length on off, Oshada Fernando punches of the back foot to covers.
Good length outside off, Oshada Fernando offers no shot at it.
This one is full outside off, Oshada Fernando gets a good stride forward and plays it towards cover.
Hasan Ali serves this one really slow and outside off from a good length. Oshada Fernando does not play a shot and the ball reaches the keeper on the bounce.
On a good length outside off, Oshada Fernando slashes this straight to the point fielder.
This one is full and angled in from outside off, Oshada Fernando clips this towards mid-wicket for a single.
Floted on middle, turning away. Oshada Fernando punches it of his back foot to point.
Slowr through the air on middle, Oshada Fernando fends it back to the bowler.
Flatter delivery on leg, Oshada Fernando knocks it to the leg side.
Tossed up on off, Oshada Fernando goes for the sweep but gets an insied edge onto his pads. Lucky for him that he got some bat on it.
Floated on middle and leg, Oshada Fernando works it from the inner half through square leg for one.
On middle, blocked out.
Agha Salman strarts with a tossed up delivery on off, turning in sharply. Oshada Fernando misses his flicks and gets hit on the pads.
Floated on off, Oshada Fernando uses his feet to work this towards mid-wicket but gets an inside edge and the ball goes towards fine leg. They cross.
Slower through the air on off, turning in. Kusal Mendis blocks it of his back foot.
Full outside off, Kusal Mendis drives it mid off.
A bit short outside off , Kusal Mendis dabs it towards backward point for a single.
Flatter and quciker on leg, Oshada Fernando eases it to long on for another single. They are scoring at a good rate.
Tossed up on middle, Oshada Fernando opens the face of his bat and pushes it towards cover-point region for one.
Full and on middle and off, Kusal Mendis makes room and drives it to covers.
RIPPER! This is tossed up on middle, turning away sharply. Kusal Mendis leans on for the defense but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Floated on off, Kusal Mendis knocks it short covers.
TURN AND BOUNCE! Yasir Shah pushes this on on middle, a bit short, it drifts away from the right hander. Kusal Mendis tries to play the cut but gets beaten on the outside edge again.
Floated on middle, Kusal Mendis blocks it to the leg side.
Tossed up down the leg, Oshada Fernando thinks about the reverse sweep but decides to leave it in the end.
Floated around off, Oshada Fernando blocks it onto the pitch.
Full and on middle, Oshada Fernando dabs it back to the bowler.
Full again o off, Oshada Fernando uses his feet and drills it straight to the bowler.
Oshada Fernando finds the bowler again. This is floated on off, Oshada Fernando gets to the pitch of the ball and hits it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Oshada Fernando flicks it through square leg for one.
Tossed up on middle, Oshada Fernando defends it well.
Sharp turn! This is pushed slower through the air, turning away sharply, Oshada Fernando gets forward to block but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On middle, blocked out.
Tossed up on middle, Oshada Fernando tries to sweep but gets a top edge but the ball lands safely in the deep square leg region. The batters get a couple of runs.
Floated on middle and off, Oshada Fernando blocks it to the off side.

Beatiful Delivery! Yasir Shah pushes this one a bit quicker on middle, turning away again. Oshada Fernando is invited to play at it but the ball just goes past the outside edge. Yasir Shah is looking dangerous.
Tossed up, outside off. Mendis comes forward to block with his bat and pad together but misses and it lobs in the hands of short leg. No bat there.
Fuller and on off, pushed through covers for a single.
On middle, fuller, eased down to mid on. Good stop there.
Flatter and spinning in around off. Fernando blocks it.
A loopy ball on middle. Kept out.
Angles it full and on middle. Fernando bunts it to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off. Mendis pushes it to covers.
A proper leg-spinner, full and outside off. Mendis gets his pad in front and shoulders arms.
This one is much closer! Full and landing around off before spinning away. Mendis is beaten on the outside edge as he prods to defend.
Floated ball outside off, played to covers.
Pushed through fuller, on off, Mendis drives it to mid off.
Keeps bowling around the off stump region, on a fuller side. Mendis lunges and blocks it out.
Very full and on middle. Fernando steps forward to defend it.
Slides it full and around leg. Fernando skips down and tucks off the outer half of the bat to square leg. One.
Drops it short and outside off. Mendis defends off the back foot.
This one spins onto the pads. Mendis hangs on the back foot to block it on the leg side.
Three runs! Shorter one, outside off. Mendis waits and dabs it late past backward point. The fielder in the deep runs to his left, dives but fails to stop it cleanly. Three runs.
Flatter ball, around middle and leg. Fernando keeps it out.
FOUR! Loosener! A rank long hop from Shah, outside off. Mendis cuts it through point and it races into the fence.
Tossed up on off. Defended out.
A loopy ball, full and on middle. Mendis leans and blocks it.
Fuller length, this one lands around off and spins away. Mendis pounces to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Pitched up on middle. Mendis stays back to dead bat it.
Slower, flighted, angling on off. Mendis blocks it on the front foot.
Fuller ball on middle, nudged to mid-wicket.
A single taken as this is full and Fernando bunts it to square leg.
Bowls it quicker, full and on middle. Mendis makes a confident block.
Now serves it outside off. Mendis blocks it again as he reaches to the pitch of the ball.
Tossed up on middle. Mendis eases it to long on for one.
This one is angling down the leg side. Fernando gets his back leg to kick it away.
Yasir Shah bowls this a fraction short outside off, Kusal Mendis slaps this to the cover-point fielder.
Serves this full outside off, Kusal Mendis lunges forward to defend towards point.
FOUR! Sri Lanka have been great at putting away poor deliveries! This is really full and angling down leg, Kusal Mendis sweeps this towards deep backward square for another boundary!
This one is tossed up full on middle, Kusal Mendis defends this down the pitch.
Yasir Shah goes short and pitches this on leg. The ball turns sharply and Kusal Mendis does well to fend this back towards the bowler.
Short once again and Yasir Shah is getting ample turn. Pitching on leg and turning away, Kusal Mendis does well to leave this one alone.
Agha Salman tosses this up full outside off, Oshada Fernando shimmies down the wicket and knocks the ball towards long on for a run.

This is full outside off, Kusal Mendis comes forward to drive and gets a bottom edge that rolls to the left of the keeper. He collects and flings the ball on the stumps but Kusal Mendis gets back in time.
This is short and on off, Kusal Mendis goes back and pulls the ball towards deep square leg fro a single.
Down the wicket once again to catch the ball on the full outside off. Works it to deep cover for a single.
This one is short as well and delivered outside off, Kusal Mendis goes back to pull but this time mistimes it to the mid-wicket fielder.

The ball pitches outside off and keeps it line, Kusal Mendis looks to defend but does so off soft hands and gets an outside edge. The ball drops in front of first slip. Umpire Erasmus is writing something on his note pad after which he calls for Lunch!
Yasir Shah flights this one full outside off, Oshada Fernando begins with a solid defensive shot.

OUT! CAUGHT! Straight after the break, Pakistan have a breakthrough! We have seen this ample times in Test cricket! Yasir Shah floats this one full angling into the stumps, Oshada Fernando goes for the drive with very little foot movement and gets a thick edge towards slip. Babar Azam takes a sharp catch low to his left and Oshada Fernando departs after a well-made half century! The umpires though get together to go upstairs and check if it was a bump ball. It came off the bat clearly. All good and that is three down.
Howout: c Babar Azam b Yasir Shah

Commentary: Turning delivery served full outside off, Angelo Mathews fends this on the front foot.
This one is tossed up outside off, Angelo Mathews drives this firmly towards cover.

Yasir Shah serves this full outside off, Angelo Mathews plays this with soft hands towards cover-point and rushes across for a single. Kusal Mendis would have been in trouble had the throw been better.
This on is served full and outside off, Kusal Mendis works this straight to the cover fielder.
Agha Salman serves this short and spinning in from outside off, Angelo Mathews covers the line of the ball and defends solidly.
This is full now outside off, Angelo Mathews places this through cover-point for a single.

FOUR! Loose once again from Pakistan and Kusal Mendis makes most of it! Agha Salman bowls half-tracker  in line with the stump. Kusal Mendis has all the time in the world to go on his back foot and pull to deep square leg for a boundary! Pakistan have conceded runs far too freely this innings.
Full outside off, Kusal Mendis defends this to the left of the bowler.

This is a fraction short and spinning into the stumps, Kusal Mendis goes on his back foot and punches it to deep cover for a single. Brings up his half-century and this has been a good inning! He will be hoping to make the most of this and convert it into a century!
This one is served short outside off, Angelo Mathews uses the crease and goes back to guide this through point for a single.
Yasir Shah flights this full outside off, Kusal Mendis defends this to the cover region.
Yasir Shah serves this a touch short outside off, Kusal Mendis makes room and slaps it towards point.
This one is quicker in the air and full, just outside off. Kusal Mendis fends this towards cover-point.
Full once again outside off, driven straight to the cover fielder.
Shorter in length and outside off, guided past point for a single.
This is full outside off, Angelo Mathews fends this one solidly.
Slightly shorter on leg, Kusal Mendis dabs it past short leg for one.
FOUR! Poor delivery from Agha Salman. This is short again on leg, Angelo Mathews pulls this past square leg for a boundary.
Flatter and on middle, Angelo Mathews drives it to mid-wicket.
Full again on off, Angelo Mathews blocks it to the off side.
Tossed up on off, Angelo Mathews steps out and defends it to silly point.
A bit short again on middle, drifting down the leg. Angelo Mathews works it through square leg for one.
Tossed up on middle, drifting away. Angelo Mathews pushes it towards the bowler.
Short and on off, turning a bit away. Angelo Mathews dabs it to point from the back foot.
Full and around off, Angelo Mathews drives it straight towards mid off.
Flighted delivery on middle, Angelo Mathews leans on defend it down the pitch.
On middle, blocked out.
This is short and on off, turning away. Angelo Mathews makes room and cuts it of his back foot thorugh cover-point region for one.
Tossed up on off, turning in. Kusal Mendis blocks it of his back foot back to the bowler.
Short and on leg, Kamindu Mendis knocks it to backward short leg.
Short again on middle and leg, Kusal Mendis pulls it through square leg for one.
Full and on off, Angelo Mathews blocks it to the off side.
Full again but down the leg this time, Angelo Mathews goes down and sweeps it towards fine leg for a single.
Floated on off from 'round the wicket, drifting away. Kusal Mendis punches it of his back foot through covers for a single.

Tossed up on off, turning away. Kusal Mendis goes to defend but gets deceived by the turn and it takes the outside edge, just goes past the first slip towards third man. The batters takes a couple of runs.
Full and on middle and leg, Kusal Mendis flicks it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Nice delivery again. This floated on off, turning away a bit. Kusal Mendis leans on only to leave it.
FOUR! Brilliant shot! This is full and on middle , Kusal Mendis goes down and sweeps it hard towards deep square leg fence for a boundary.
A bit short around off, turning away a bit too much. Kusal Mendis leaves it alone.

EDGED AND FOUR! This is tossed up on off, turning away. Kusal Mendis gets forward to block it but only manages a thick outside edge. The ball goes just past the first slip and races away to the third man fence for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, turning in. Angelo Mathews blocks it to the off side.
Flighted delivery on off, Angelo Mathews gets to the pitch of it and defends.
A bit short and drifting into the pads, Angelo Mathews tucks it away to square leg for one.
Floated on middle and leg, Kusal Mendis knocks it to the leg side.
Slightly shorter on middle and leg, Kusal Mendis taps it to leg slip.
Tossed up on middle, Kusal Mendis steps out and takes it on the full and flicks it wide of mid-wicket for a single.
Runs are coming nicely for the hosts now! Flatter and outside off, punched off the back foot to covers for one.
Tossed up angling on off, pushed to covers.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Nawaz gets his man on the third ball of his new spell. Much needed one! This is too short and outside off, turning away, it is there to be hit but there is extra bounce as well. Mathews has to reach for it a bit as he tries to cut but gets an outside edge and Babar Azam at first slip takes it with ease to his left. Pakistan need to build on this now.
Howout: c Babar Azam b Mohammad Nawaz

Commentary: Superb follow-up delivery! Tossed up, angling outside off and turns away. Chandimal prods and defends inside the line. He misses completely.
Swing and a miss! Chandimal pre-meditates as he tries to sweep but Nawaz serves it full and way outside off. Missed it again.
Eventful over from Mohammad Nawaz comes to an end! Again this is full and outside off, turning away enough to beat Chandimal's outside edge.
Tossed up, around off and spinning in. Mendis gets back to block it.
Much fuller this time, on middle, drilled to long on for a single.
Chandimal is off the mark! Tossed up on off. Chandimal defends it towards silly mid off and takes a quick single.
Slanting and spinning onto the pads. Mendis tucks it to short leg.
Floated ball on off. Mendis leans and blocks it.
FOUR! Gorgeous shot! A low full toss and around off. Mendis makes the most of it as he drives it to deep cover. Naseem Shah from deep point runs across, slides but fails to stop it.
Fuller ball, outside off, swept to deep square leg for a single.
Angles a flatter ball on middle and it skids on. Mendis clears his front leg and defends it.
Tight, quicker and on top of off. Blocked out.
Too full, flighted and it is driven to covers for a run.
Very full and outside off. Chandimal sweeps as he gets inside the line to deep square leg for one.
Tossed up, outside off. Mendis prods and dabs it to backward point.
Tossed up, lands on midde and spins away sharply. Chandimal defends it late to point.
Too full, floats one on middle. Chandimal drives it to mid off for a run.
Shorter and way outside off. Mendis slaps it to deep point for a run.
Good delivery! better line, It lands on leg and spins on off. Chandimal gets inside the line to block it.
Flatter and outside off, punched through covers for a single.
Length ball, around off. Mendis rocks back and punches it to point.
Slants one around off, slower a bit. Chandimal punches it to covers.
Tossed up, angling outside off. Chandimal looks to sweep as he sits across but misses and gets hit on the pads. Impact was outside off.
Drifts a full ball on leg. Chandimal flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Drops it short and on middle, straightens up. Mendis blocks on the back foot.
Gives a bit of width, shorter side. Mendis punches it through covers for a single.

Perfect delivery to end the over! Angles a full ball, around off and it turns away sharply. Chandimal takes a stride forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. Pakistan were thinking to refer it upstairs but the captain wasn't quite convinced.

OUT! TIMBER! What a screamer of a delivery! This one is right from the book of great leg spin deliveries! Yasir Shah floats this slightly back of a length outside the leg stump, the ball turns sharply and beats the outside edge to crash against the top of the off pole. Mendis has no idea how to play this one. What a delivery and Sri Lanka have half their side in the shed!
Howout: b Yasir Shah

Commentary: This is short as well, and spinning from off, Dhananjaya de Silva works this towards cover-point.
Yasir Shah goes full on middle, Dinesh Chandimal sweeps this towards deep square leg for a single.
Yasir Shah serves a googly full and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva reads the delivery and defends solidly.
This is short and spinning wide outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva mistimes it towards cover.
This one is full outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva strokes it straight to mid off.
Mohammad Nawaz serves this full outside off, Dinesh Chandimal plays it with soft hands toward cover with and rushes across for a single.
This one is full as well, Dhananjaya de Silva defends this towards cover on the back foot.
Full and in line with the stumps, Dhananjaya de Silva fends this down the pitch.

Mohammad Nawaz floats this full and angling down leg, Dhananjaya de Silva looks to sweep and misses. Hits the pads and the Pakistan players appeal! The umpire reckons it is going down leg. They do not review.

FOUR! This one is beautifully placed! Mohammad Nawaz shortens his length outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva goes deep in the crease and find this gap through cover ;point for a boundary! This one is not hit hard, just placed with great timing!
Shorter in length and pitching on off, Dhananjaya de Silva rocks back and punches it towards cover.
Yasir Shah looks in good rhythm! Getting some good turn now from this wicket. Serves this full outside leg and gets the ball to turn past the outside edge. Well collected by the keeper.
Goes full outside leg, Dinesh Chandimal sweeps this towards fine leg for a single. The players appeal but that has come off the gloves.
Yasir Shah serves that full outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva taps it towards cover and looks for a single. Dinesh Chandimal sends him back.
This is full outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva fends this towards point.

SIX! That is one way to negotiate spin! Dhananjaya de Silva gets down the wicket and catches the ball on the full in line with the stumps. This one flies high and handsome over the long off boundary for a biggie! Dhananjaya de Silva is taking the attack to Yasir Shah!

Beaten! Good flight from Yasir Shah as he serves this full outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva pushes at the ball and misses the line completely. Beats the outside edge and is collected well by the keeper.
Mohammad Nawaz delivers this full and in line with the stumps. Dinesh Chandimal defends this back down the pitch.
Full and angling down leg, Dinesh Chandimal sweeps and the ball hits the pad and lobs up to Mohammad Rizwan behind the wicket.
Mohammad Nawaz flights this full outside off, Dinesh Chandimal taps it towards cover.

SIX! Sri Lanka are choosing to counterattack now! This one is served full and angling into the pads, Dinesh Chandimal gets on his knee and swats it towards deep mid-wicket for another big hit! Sri Lanka are not going to block around and wait for an unplayable delivery!
This one is quicker in the air served short and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal looks to slash at this and gets beaten by the extra bounce.
Mohammad Nawaz serves this full and going down leg, Dinesh Chandimal sweeps hard and hits the shin of leg slip and rolls to deep backward square leg for a single.
Yasir Shah slights this full on outside off, Dinesh Chandimal strokes this towards mid off.

FOUR! This is a gift once again! Yasir Shah serves this short and wide outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva waits on it and cuts it late past backward point for a boundary to third man! These are easy runs on a difficult wicket!
This one is served full and in line with the stumps, Dhananjaya de Silva flicks the ball through mid-wicket for a brace.
Short and wide outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva looks to guide this towards third man but hits it straight to gully.
Yasir Shah has been a touch too short this over as this one is pitching on off and turning further away. Dhananjaya de Silva thumps it through to deep cover for a couple of runs.
Sharp turn from outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva leaves this one alone.
SIX! HUGE! This tossed up on middle, Dinesh Chandimal smokes it over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie. This is brilliant batting from him.
A bit short around off, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it through cover-point for one.
Short again outide off, Dhananjaya de Silva works it to deep point for a single.
Flighted delivery on off, turning away. Dinesh Chandimal guides it to point.
Tossed up on off, turning away a bit. Dinesh Chandimal knocks it towards point.
Slightly shorter outside off, Dinesh Chandimal cuts it hard to point and calls for a single. There is a misfield and the batters scampers across for the second as well.

OUT! CLEANED UP! Yasir Shah bowls this a bit quicker and full on middle, holds its line and skidding onto the stumps. Dhananjaya de Silva goes on the back foot to block but plays down the wrong line. The ball brushes his front pad and goes crashing onto the stumps. Yasir Shah once again getting the wicket. Sri Lanka are six down now.
Howout: b Yasir Shah

Commentary: Darts this one on leg, Niroshan Dickwella tries to play but gets hit on the pads.
Floated on off, Niroshan Dickwella goes for the sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Full on middle, Niroshan Dickwella sweeps it to deep square leg for one. He gets off the mark.
Arm ball on middle and leg, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it of his back foot to square leg for one.
Tossed up on leg, Niroshan Dickwella revers sweeps it towards deep point for a single.
Tossed up on off, Niroshan Dickwella goes down for the sweep and gets a top edge towards backward square leg. They cross.
Tossed up on middle, Dinesh Chandimal blocks it down the pitch.
Flatter delivery outside off, no turn. Dinesh Chandimal leaves it alone.
Slightly shorter outside off, turning away. Dinesh Chandimal dabs it past cover-point for a single.
Tossed up on off, Niroshan Dickwella gets forwards and knocks it towards mid on.
FOUR! Clever from Niroshan Dickwella. This floated on off, Niroshan Dickwella plays the reverse sweep past the first slip fielder towards the third man fence for a boundary.
Tossed up on middle, Dinesh Chandimal blocks it to the off side.
A bit short on leg, Dinesh Chandimal stays back and punches it to long off for one.
Floated on middle, turning in, Niroshan Dickwella goes down and sweeps it fin towards backward square for a single.
This is short outside off, Dinesh Chandimal cuts it through cover-point for another single.

FOUR! Beautifully played. This is quicker and flatter on middle, Niroshan Dickwella again sweeps it hard towards deep square leg. The fielder misjudges and dives early to his right. The ball goes past him and races away to the boundary.
Tossed up on off, Niroshan Dickwella blocks it out.
Slower through the air on middle, Dinesh Chandimal guides to point from his back foot for a run.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! Mohammad Nawaz gets his fourth. This is floated outside off, spinning in. Niroshan Dickwella tries the reverse sweep again but only manages an inside edge. The ball hits the ground and goes onto hit the leg stump. Sri Lanka in huge trouble now.
Howout: b Mohammad Nawaz

Commentary: Tossed up on middle and off, turning away. Ramesh Mendis leaves it alone.
On middle, blocked out.
This is tossed up again on off, Ramesh Mendis opens the face of his bat and knocks it to point.

Darts this one down the leg, Ramesh Mendis misses his sweep and the ball goes straight and hits the keeper's pad and goes up in the air, Mohammad Rizwan tries to grab it but fails to do so. Mohammad Nawaz thinks that the batter got a glove on it and is dissappointed the catch is not completed.
Tossed up, on off, defended to covers.
A leggie, lands on leg and spins around off. Chandimal reads it well as he blocks off the back foot.
Too full and on off. Defended on the front foot.
Slightly short and outside off. Chandimal punches it to deep cover for one.
Tossed up, outside off. Mendis steps down and across to sweep it to deep square leg for one.
Slows it up, on middle, pushed to long off for a run.
Flighted full, outside off, driven to covers.
An arm ball, slanting on leg. Chandimal tucks it to deep mid-wicket for a single. Mohammad Rizwan looks a bit in pain as the ball bounces and hits him near his right arm and deflects onto the throat.
This is short and outside off, no turn. Mendis tries to defend in the wrong line.
Shorter and again extra bounce. Mendis works it through covers for a run.
Angles a full ball on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller ball, slanting around off. Chandimal prods and blocks it.
Full ball, just outside off, swept to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
On off, blocked out.
This is full and outside off, a leggie. Left alone.
FOUR! Ramesh Mendis gets his first boundary! This one is a fraction short and angled into the stumps, Ramesh Mendis rocks back and pulls this through mid-wicket fora boundary!
Full outside off, Ramesh Mendis fends this towards the cover region.
Tossed up full and on middle, Ramesh Mendis clips this towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Fuller ball on off. Blocked out.
This is full and Mendis pushes it to covers.
Flatter and outside off. Left alone.
Slides one down the leg side. Mendis sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Angles a full ball from wide of the crease. Chandimal hangs back and keeps it out.
Better from Nawaz! Length ball, outside off, angling in and spins away. Chandimal lunges to defend but misses comprehensively.
FOUR! Azam starts with shorter ball, outside off and spinning in. Mendis punches hard off the back foot and to deep cover for a boundary. 250 up for the Lankans.
Tossed up, around off and turning in. Mendis tries to defend but this one spins sharply and hits him on the pads. An appeal but it was sliding down.
Short again. It is slapped to deep point for a run.
A loopy ball on off. Mendis blocks it out on the front foot.
Drops it short and way outside off. Mendis opens the face of the bat and dabs it past first slip and to third man for a brace.
A single to end the over and the session as well! Shorter and outside off, cut away to deep point for one. That will be Tea as well!
Mohammad Nawaz begins with a full delivery outside off, Ramesh Mendis strokes this towards point.
This is flighted full outside off, Ramesh Mendis watches the ball go straight into the keeper's gloves.
Mohammad Nawaz goes short and wide outside off, Ramesh Mendis stands tall and punches this to deep cover for a single.
Mohammad Nawaz flights this full on middle and leg, Dinesh Chandimal defends this back to the bowler.
Tossed up full outside off, This one is defended towards mid off by Dinesh Chandimal.
Mohammad Nawaz continues bowling full outside off, Dinesh Chandimal taps this towards cover-point and rushes across for a single.
Yasir Shah begins with a full delivery outside off, Dinesh Chandimal works this to the right of point for a single.
This is short and turning wide outside off, Ramesh Mendis hits this on his back foot to the left of cover for a single.

FOUR! In the air and runs away for a boundary! This is tossed up full and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal slaps this over the cover fielder and gets four runs! Dinesh Chandimal is balancing defense with some attack!
This is also short and turning wide from off stump, Dinesh Chandimal uses the crease and works this through cover-point for a single.
Shorter in length and angling into the pads, Ramesh Mendis clips this towards deep square leg for single.
Flights this full outside off, Dinesh Chandimal punches this straight to cover.
Mohammad Nawaz serves this short and outside off, Ramesh Mendis defends on his back foot towards mid off.
This is full and on middle, Ramesh Mendis clips this towards mid-wicket.
Full delivery outside off, Ramesh Mendis strides forward and defends this towards short cover.

OUT! BOWLED! The off pole has been pegged back here! A five wicket haul for Mohammad Nawaz and he breaks this stubborn partnership! This is a fraction short outside off and comes in sharply. Ramesh Mendis looks to make room to cut but the ball is too close to his body goes on to hit the top of off stump! That is the first five wicket haul for Mohammad Nawaz in Test cricket!
Howout: b Mohammad Nawaz

Commentary: Tossed up on off, Maheesh Theekshana blocks it towards short mid off.
Tossed up again on middle, Maheesh Theekshana plays a solid defense on the off side.
This is served full and pitching on middle, Dinesh Chandimal nudges it towards backward square leg for a single.
Flights this one full and well outside off. Maheesh Theekshana leaves this one alone.
Yasir Shah goes full once again and closer to the stumps. Maheesh Theekshana taps it towards point and looks for a single that is not there.
Serves this one full and wide outside off. The turn takes it further away and Maheesh Theekshana lets it go.
This one is flighted full on middle, Maheesh Theekshana fends it back to the bowler.
Yasir Shah continues to bowl full and this is on off, Maheesh Theekshana taps it back towards the bowler.
Naseem Shah starts off with a good length delivery outside off, Dinesh Chandimal defends this towards cover.
On a good length once again and just outside off, Dinesh Chandimal looks to defend and gets an inside edge onto his foot.
NO BALL! Serves this one fuller outside off, Dinesh Chandimal strokes this to deep cover-point for a single. He has overstepped though and a no ball has been called!

This is served on a good length outside off, Maheesh Theekshana is drawn into a shot and gets a thick edge that falls just short of gully. Maheesh Theekshana needs to apply himself here and get Dinesh Chandimal on strike.
Naseem Shah bangs this one in short and in line with the stumps. Maheesh Theekshana does not even need to duck under this one but wide has no been called.
This one is on a good length and outside off, Maheesh Theekshana knocks this towards cover.
This is short as well and better directed. Maheesh Theekshana gets low under this delivery and lets it through to the keeper.

Good running between the wickets here. This is floated on middle, turning away. Dinesh Chandimal waits for the ball and guides to the vacant third man area. The fielder gives a chase but the batters run three.
Maheesh Theekshana gets off the mark, This is tossed up on off, Maheesh Theekshana pushes it through covers for a comfortable brace.
Full and on middle, Maheesh Theekshana blocks it out.
Quicker and flatter on middle, Maheesh Theekshana knocks it back to the bowler.
Slower through the air on middle, turning in. Maheesh Theekshana once again is solid in his defense.
On middle, blocked out.
Bangs in a short ball around off, Dinesh Chandimal ducks under it.
Back of a length delivery on off, Dinesh Chandimal cuts it close to his body towards deep point for a single.
Goes full this time on off, Maheesh Theekshana drives it gently to mid off and picks up a single.
Short again on leg, angling away. Dinesh Chandimal pulls it to fine leg for one.
Serves this full and down the leg, Maheesh Theekshana works it to mid-wicket.
Full again on middle and off, Maheesh Theekshana goes to drive it to mid off but gets an inside edge and the ball rolls towards mid on. They cross.
Slower through the air outside off, turnin away a bit too much. Maheesh Theekshana leaves it alone.
Floated on middle, Maheesh Theekshana pushes it towards cover-point for on.
Full again on middle, Dinesh Chandimal knocks it to silly mid off.
Floated on off, Dinesh Chandimal blocks it ut.
BEATEN!! This is bowled slower through the air on middle, turning away. Dinesh Chandimal gets forward to block but gets beaten on the inside edge.
Flatter and quicker on leg, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
Starts with a bouncer again but down the leg, Dinesh Chandimal ducks underneath it.
Good length on off, shaping in, Dinesh Chandimal blocks it with the bottom part of his willow onto the ground. The ball hits the ground and then goes onto hit him on the chest.

Another half-century for Dinesh Chandimal. He is in some form. This is on a length and on off, Dinesh Chandimal knocks it with soft hands to covers for a single. Dinesh Chandimal once again is the man for Sri Lanka and he has looked like he is playing on a different pitch. He will look to score as many runs as possible and extend the lead.
Bangs in a bouncer on leg, Maheesh Theekshana ducks under it.
Short ball again on off, angling away a bit. Maheesh Theekshana tries to cut it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Good delivery this time. This is short again on middle, angling into the body. Maheesh Theekshana does well to move out of the way and lets it go the keeper.
Floated on middle, Dinesh Chandimal blocks it with his inner half to the leg side.
Tossed up on middle, turning away. Dinesh Chandimal works it through mid-wicket for a run.
Well left! This is tossed up again on middle and off, turning away. Maheesh Theekshana watches it and leaves it alone.
On off, kept out.
Floated on off again, Maheesh Theekshana defends it to silly point.
Slower through the air on off, Maheesh Theekshana opens the face of his bat and guides it towards third man for a brace.
On a length and outside off. Chandimal punches it to covers.
Length ball, outside off. Chandimal pushes it off the outer half to point for one.
A length ball, around off and it swings back in very late. Theekshana gets hit on the pads as he tries to fend it away.
An inswinging fuller ball on middle. Theekshana lofts it over the bowler's head. Afridi from mid off makes a tumbling stop. One.
On a length and on off, nips in. Chandimal adjusts quickly as he drops it to covers. One.
Sharp single! Full ball with sharp inward shape, on middle. Theekshana pushes it to mid off and calls for a quick single. Afridi has a shy at the keeper's end but misses.
Tossed up, sliding on middle.  Theekshana pushes it to covers.
Slows it up, flatter and angling on the pads. Theekshana seems to miss his flick. It lobs off the pads in the hands of short leg. An appeal follows but nothing given.
Shorter and on middle. Blocked out.
Keeps bowling onto the stumps. Theekshana stays back to defend.
Goes wide of the crease and serves a full ball on off. Theekshana pushes it to covers.
Flighted full and around middle. Blocked out.
Full ball, around off and swinging in. Chandimal watchfully pushes it to mid off.
FOUR! That is a gorgeous shot! Chandimal anticipated the line to be full and he drives with the swing through the line and past mid on, to his left for a boundary.
A yorker but sliding down, whipped behind square on the leg side for a couple.
The lead gets past the 300 mark! Same delivery as the previous one. Chandimal flicks it in the vacant deep mid-wicket region for a couple. Shah need to drag his length ball.
On a length and outside off, this one straightens up. Chandimal is not fully through as he tries to defend, misses it.
Chandimal will keep the strike. Fuller and nips back in on off, it is pushed to mid off for a quick single.
